WEBVTT

00:00:33.256 --> 00:00:34.606 A:middle
&gt;&gt; My desk is on the seventh

00:00:34.646 --> 00:00:35.666 A:middle
floor, if you need anything, you

00:00:35.666 --> 00:00:36.396 A:middle
can call me.

00:00:37.016 --> 00:00:37.946 A:middle
Make sure to keep your ID with

00:00:37.946 --> 00:00:39.196 A:middle
you because you're going to need

00:00:39.196 --> 00:00:40.716 A:middle
to badge in every time you

00:00:40.716 --> 00:00:41.296 A:middle
reenter.

00:00:41.636 --> 00:00:43.376 A:middle
The cafeteria is on the fourth

00:00:43.506 --> 00:00:44.886 A:middle
floor and we generally take

00:00:44.886 --> 00:00:45.886 A:middle
lunch about 12:30.

00:00:46.486 --> 00:00:48.106 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Cool. This is where I'm

00:00:48.176 --> 00:00:48.426 A:middle
sitting?

00:00:48.566 --> 00:00:49.396 A:middle
&gt;&gt; For now, yeah.

00:00:49.866 --> 00:00:51.046 A:middle
With the big move coming up,

00:00:51.096 --> 00:00:52.776 A:middle
it's kind of crazy around here.

00:00:53.286 --> 00:00:55.506 A:middle
I promise it's only temporary.

00:00:55.666 --> 00:00:56.256 A:middle
&gt;&gt; All right, thank you.

00:00:56.336 --> 00:00:56.856 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Mm-hmm.

00:01:04.516 --> 00:01:31.516 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:01:32.516 --> 00:01:45.516 A:middle
[ Foreign Language ]

00:01:46.516 --> 00:01:48.516 A:middle
[ Baby Crying ]

00:01:49.516 --> 00:01:54.156 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:01:54.656 --> 00:01:56.516 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Come let us in, we need

00:01:56.686 --> 00:01:56.836 A:middle
Airbnb.

00:01:57.046 --> 00:01:57.676 A:middle
&gt;&gt; This is not an Airbnb.

00:01:59.566 --> 00:02:00.576 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Where are we, man?

00:02:00.846 --> 00:02:01.456 A:middle
&gt;&gt; I don't know.

00:02:01.806 --> 00:02:04.106 A:middle
I don't even know what city

00:02:04.786 --> 00:02:05.116 A:middle
we're in.

00:02:05.116 --> 00:02:05.976 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Look out!

00:02:06.516 --> 00:02:16.626 A:middle
[ Music and Noise ]

00:02:17.126 --> 00:02:18.546 A:middle
&gt;&gt; World leaders are declaring a

00:02:18.716 --> 00:02:20.616 A:middle
global state of emergency until

00:02:20.616 --> 00:02:22.156 A:middle
the app situation can be

00:02:22.236 --> 00:02:22.536 A:middle
resolved.

00:02:24.616 --> 00:02:25.776 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Selfies, anybody?

00:02:25.776 --> 00:02:26.856 A:middle
Selfies, selfies!

00:02:28.726 --> 00:02:30.846 A:middle
&gt;&gt; The apocalypse is nigh!

00:02:30.846 --> 00:02:33.416 A:middle
The apocalypse is nigh!

00:02:33.646 --> 00:02:36.816 A:middle
&gt;&gt; OK. Who wants to go first?

00:02:37.016 --> 00:02:39.016 A:middle
[ Screams ]

00:02:39.176 --> 00:02:41.176 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:02:41.336 --> 00:02:42.866 A:middle
&gt;&gt; iTunes, get your iTunes.

00:02:45.656 --> 00:02:46.636 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Do you think we should have

00:02:46.636 --> 00:02:47.746 A:middle
gone with the puppy face?

00:02:47.746 --> 00:02:48.816 A:middle
&gt;&gt; I just ate this whole pizza

00:02:48.816 --> 00:02:49.426 A:middle
by myself.

00:02:50.496 --> 00:02:53.026 A:middle
Hashtag too delicious to share.

00:02:53.176 --> 00:02:55.286 A:middle
Hashtag pizza emoji.

00:02:55.816 --> 00:02:57.156 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Farm Ville 2 right here, yo.

00:02:57.586 --> 00:02:58.766 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Hashtag eat the food.

00:02:59.086 --> 00:03:02.046 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Brian, looking for Brian.

00:03:02.046 --> 00:03:02.826 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Hashtag does anybody want a

00:03:02.856 --> 00:03:02.976 A:middle
slice?

00:03:03.516 --> 00:03:18.516 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:03:19.516 --> 00:03:29.896 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:03:30.396 --> 00:03:30.876 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Good morning.

00:03:32.516 --> 00:03:35.356 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:03:35.856 --> 00:03:37.806 A:middle
I'm so glad that really can't

00:03:37.806 --> 00:03:38.206 A:middle
happen.

00:03:39.696 --> 00:03:42.946 A:middle
Welcome to WWDC.

00:03:42.946 --> 00:03:44.586 A:middle
It's great to be back in San

00:03:44.586 --> 00:03:46.736 A:middle
Jose, the heart of Silicon

00:03:46.736 --> 00:03:48.606 A:middle
Valley and right down the street

00:03:48.796 --> 00:03:51.346 A:middle
from Apple and our new campus.

00:03:51.346 --> 00:03:53.126 A:middle
It's been 15 years since we held

00:03:53.126 --> 00:03:54.536 A:middle
the developer conference in San

00:03:54.536 --> 00:03:56.906 A:middle
Jose and an awful lot has

00:03:56.906 --> 00:03:57.616 A:middle
changed.

00:03:58.076 --> 00:03:59.556 A:middle
But the one thing that hasn't

00:03:59.556 --> 00:04:01.556 A:middle
changed is our commitment to the

00:04:01.556 --> 00:04:03.416 A:middle
developer community and our

00:04:03.416 --> 00:04:05.896 A:middle
ability to do amazing things

00:04:05.896 --> 00:04:06.386 A:middle
together.

00:04:07.466 --> 00:04:11.226 A:middle
This is going to be the best and

00:04:11.226 --> 00:04:13.636 A:middle
biggest WWDC ever.

00:04:14.516 --> 00:04:20.796 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:04:21.296 --> 00:04:24.136 A:middle
Every year, we host WWDC to

00:04:24.136 --> 00:04:26.746 A:middle
bring Apple engineers and our

00:04:26.746 --> 00:04:29.066 A:middle
amazing developers together on

00:04:29.066 --> 00:04:31.166 A:middle
our collective mission to change

00:04:31.166 --> 00:04:31.716 A:middle
the world.

00:04:32.516 --> 00:04:34.566 A:middle
And I'm pleased to tell you, the

00:04:34.696 --> 00:04:36.936 A:middle
Apple Developer community has

00:04:36.986 --> 00:04:38.406 A:middle
never been more vibrant.

00:04:39.166 --> 00:04:41.796 A:middle
We now have 16 million

00:04:41.796 --> 00:04:43.196 A:middle
registered developers in the

00:04:43.196 --> 00:04:44.526 A:middle
program around the world.

00:04:45.096 --> 00:04:47.876 A:middle
And we added three million last

00:04:47.876 --> 00:04:48.706 A:middle
year alone.

00:04:49.616 --> 00:04:51.906 A:middle
We've got 5300 developers here

00:04:51.906 --> 00:04:54.956 A:middle
this morning, our largest group

00:04:55.156 --> 00:04:55.636 A:middle
ever.

00:04:57.226 --> 00:04:59.066 A:middle
We have attendees this morning

00:04:59.066 --> 00:05:02.126 A:middle
from 75 countries across the

00:05:02.126 --> 00:05:02.706 A:middle
world.

00:05:03.096 --> 00:05:04.816 A:middle
It's truly a worldwide

00:05:04.816 --> 00:05:06.726 A:middle
conference.

00:05:06.726 --> 00:05:08.696 A:middle
And we have the most student

00:05:08.696 --> 00:05:10.906 A:middle
developers with us this morning

00:05:11.196 --> 00:05:11.516 A:middle
ever.

00:05:12.516 --> 00:05:19.266 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:05:19.766 --> 00:05:22.646 A:middle
In fact, one of our youngest is

00:05:22.646 --> 00:05:23.686 A:middle
here this morning.

00:05:23.886 --> 00:05:29.736 A:middle
His, his name is Yuma Sorianto.

00:05:29.786 --> 00:05:31.776 A:middle
He's from Australia and he's

00:05:31.776 --> 00:05:32.996 A:middle
just 10 years old.

00:05:33.566 --> 00:05:35.946 A:middle
He started coding when he was

00:05:36.026 --> 00:05:39.596 A:middle
six and he already has five apps

00:05:39.596 --> 00:05:40.656 A:middle
on the App Store.

00:05:41.516 --> 00:05:46.336 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:05:46.836 --> 00:05:49.936 A:middle
I met Yuma yesterday and I can't

00:05:49.936 --> 00:05:51.126 A:middle
wait to see what he's going to

00:05:51.156 --> 00:05:52.936 A:middle
accomplish next.

00:05:52.936 --> 00:05:54.146 A:middle
And while we've got some great

00:05:54.146 --> 00:05:55.886 A:middle
up and coming developers like

00:05:55.946 --> 00:05:58.756 A:middle
Yuma, we got some that got a bit

00:05:58.756 --> 00:06:03.266 A:middle
of a later start, Masako.

00:06:03.346 --> 00:06:09.766 A:middle
Masako Wakamiya is just 82 years

00:06:09.766 --> 00:06:13.106 A:middle
old and she's from Japan and she

00:06:13.106 --> 00:06:15.576 A:middle
published her first app earlier

00:06:15.576 --> 00:06:16.516 A:middle
this year.

00:06:17.316 --> 00:06:17.646 A:middle
So--

00:06:18.516 --> 00:06:21.366 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:06:21.866 --> 00:06:23.156 A:middle
So, if you haven't published

00:06:23.226 --> 00:06:24.906 A:middle
yet, there is still time.

00:06:25.766 --> 00:06:27.256 A:middle
Let's give them a big round of

00:06:27.256 --> 00:06:27.886 A:middle
applause.

00:06:28.516 --> 00:06:34.386 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:06:34.886 --> 00:06:36.286 A:middle
Now, let's turn our attention to

00:06:36.286 --> 00:06:39.126 A:middle
our four incredible platforms.

00:06:39.126 --> 00:06:40.856 A:middle
Of course as you know each of

00:06:40.856 --> 00:06:42.686 A:middle
them stem from the same core

00:06:42.686 --> 00:06:45.846 A:middle
technology, but each is uniquely

00:06:45.846 --> 00:06:48.286 A:middle
expressed and designed for the

00:06:48.286 --> 00:06:50.516 A:middle
best experience for where they

00:06:50.516 --> 00:06:50.906 A:middle
work.

00:06:51.676 --> 00:06:53.696 A:middle
We keep pushing these platforms

00:06:53.696 --> 00:06:55.196 A:middle
forward giving you, the

00:06:55.196 --> 00:06:57.766 A:middle
developers, powerful tools and

00:06:57.766 --> 00:06:59.836 A:middle
opportunities to change the

00:06:59.836 --> 00:07:00.406 A:middle
world.

00:07:01.036 --> 00:07:02.856 A:middle
That's why this developer

00:07:02.856 --> 00:07:04.896 A:middle
conference is so important.

00:07:05.616 --> 00:07:07.686 A:middle
Now, we have a lot to talk about

00:07:07.686 --> 00:07:08.126 A:middle
today.

00:07:08.616 --> 00:07:10.626 A:middle
And I do mean a lot.

00:07:11.266 --> 00:07:12.966 A:middle
So, I'm dispensing with the

00:07:12.966 --> 00:07:14.636 A:middle
updates other than to tell you,

00:07:15.196 --> 00:07:16.286 A:middle
Apple is doing great.

00:07:17.516 --> 00:07:22.986 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:07:23.486 --> 00:07:26.066 A:middle
We have six important

00:07:26.096 --> 00:07:27.606 A:middle
announcements to share with you

00:07:27.606 --> 00:07:28.296 A:middle
this morning.

00:07:29.476 --> 00:07:31.776 A:middle
So, let's get right into it and

00:07:31.776 --> 00:07:34.736 A:middle
I'll start with tvOS.

00:07:35.406 --> 00:07:37.666 A:middle
We recently introduced the TV

00:07:37.666 --> 00:07:41.046 A:middle
app on Apple TV, iPhone and iPad

00:07:41.046 --> 00:07:42.746 A:middle
to create the easiest way to

00:07:42.746 --> 00:07:45.116 A:middle
discover and enjoy your TV

00:07:45.116 --> 00:07:47.156 A:middle
content from across your video

00:07:47.156 --> 00:07:49.666 A:middle
channels all in one convenient

00:07:49.666 --> 00:07:50.956 A:middle
place.

00:07:50.956 --> 00:07:52.296 A:middle
We launched it with support from

00:07:52.296 --> 00:07:54.126 A:middle
just a handful of video channels

00:07:54.376 --> 00:07:56.676 A:middle
but now, we have 50 partners

00:07:56.776 --> 00:07:58.296 A:middle
integrated into the TV app.

00:07:59.356 --> 00:08:02.246 A:middle
And today, we're really thrilled

00:08:02.246 --> 00:08:05.456 A:middle
to announce that Amazon is

00:08:05.586 --> 00:08:05.976 A:middle
coming--

00:08:06.516 --> 00:08:09.476 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:08:09.976 --> 00:08:12.016 A:middle
-- Amazon is coming to the TV

00:08:12.016 --> 00:08:14.026 A:middle
app and Apple-- and all Apple

00:08:14.146 --> 00:08:16.766 A:middle
TVs later this year with Amazon

00:08:16.766 --> 00:08:17.736 A:middle
Prime Video.

00:08:18.146 --> 00:08:19.566 A:middle
And, of course, as you know,

00:08:20.146 --> 00:08:22.656 A:middle
Prime Video provides a wealth of

00:08:22.656 --> 00:08:24.396 A:middle
great content, thousands of TV

00:08:24.396 --> 00:08:26.756 A:middle
shows and movies and some great

00:08:26.856 --> 00:08:28.476 A:middle
original content like

00:08:28.476 --> 00:08:30.916 A:middle
"Transparent", "Mozart in the

00:08:30.916 --> 00:08:32.416 A:middle
Jungle", "Man in the High

00:08:32.576 --> 00:08:35.216 A:middle
Castle" and so much more.

00:08:35.286 --> 00:08:37.486 A:middle
We are so pleased to welcome

00:08:37.486 --> 00:08:39.406 A:middle
Amazon to Apple TV.

00:08:40.516 --> 00:08:44.976 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:08:45.476 --> 00:08:46.006 A:middle
So that's tvOS.

00:08:46.176 --> 00:08:49.346 A:middle
You'll be hearing a lot more

00:08:49.346 --> 00:08:51.956 A:middle
about tvOS later this year.

00:08:53.206 --> 00:08:56.096 A:middle
Number two, let's talk about

00:08:56.166 --> 00:08:57.246 A:middle
Apple Watch.

00:08:58.016 --> 00:08:59.046 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:08:59.046 --> 00:09:02.866 A:middle
Apple Watch has had incredible

00:09:02.986 --> 00:09:04.436 A:middle
growth this past year.

00:09:04.816 --> 00:09:06.796 A:middle
In fact it's the number one

00:09:06.886 --> 00:09:09.526 A:middle
selling smartwatch by far.

00:09:09.846 --> 00:09:11.706 A:middle
And what's most important to us

00:09:11.856 --> 00:09:13.546 A:middle
is that it's number one in

00:09:13.586 --> 00:09:16.996 A:middle
customer satisfaction again by

00:09:17.136 --> 00:09:17.686 A:middle
far.

00:09:18.726 --> 00:09:20.686 A:middle
Apple Watch is designed to help

00:09:20.686 --> 00:09:22.006 A:middle
you live a healthier life.

00:09:22.356 --> 00:09:24.376 A:middle
And people are absolutely loving

00:09:24.376 --> 00:09:26.576 A:middle
the fitness capabilities, the

00:09:26.576 --> 00:09:28.626 A:middle
health capabilities, the quick

00:09:28.626 --> 00:09:32.126 A:middle
access to information and even

00:09:32.206 --> 00:09:33.676 A:middle
the ability to swim with it.

00:09:34.276 --> 00:09:37.116 A:middle
We've got some exciting updates

00:09:37.116 --> 00:09:39.426 A:middle
to the watchOS and to take you

00:09:39.516 --> 00:09:41.276 A:middle
through them, I'd like to invite

00:09:41.426 --> 00:09:42.526 A:middle
Kevin Lynch up.

00:09:42.526 --> 00:09:42.876 A:middle
Kevin?

00:09:43.516 --> 00:09:46.746 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:09:47.246 --> 00:09:47.756 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thank you, Tim.

00:09:50.736 --> 00:09:52.436 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So watchOS is moving forward

00:09:52.436 --> 00:09:53.346 A:middle
really quickly.

00:09:53.346 --> 00:09:54.686 A:middle
And I'm very excited to

00:09:54.686 --> 00:09:56.586 A:middle
introduce watchOS 4 today.

00:09:57.106 --> 00:09:58.376 A:middle
This furthers the areas that

00:09:58.376 --> 00:09:59.206 A:middle
people love.

00:09:59.206 --> 00:10:00.926 A:middle
It also introduces new ways to

00:10:00.926 --> 00:10:02.406 A:middle
make the watch more personal to

00:10:02.726 --> 00:10:02.906 A:middle
you.

00:10:03.056 --> 00:10:05.496 A:middle
Let's start with watch faces.

00:10:05.626 --> 00:10:06.806 A:middle
Now, Apple Watch is great for

00:10:06.806 --> 00:10:08.056 A:middle
quickly glancing at information.

00:10:08.056 --> 00:10:08.866 A:middle
And many people are using a

00:10:08.866 --> 00:10:10.066 A:middle
watch face like this today.

00:10:10.416 --> 00:10:11.486 A:middle
And now, you need to choose what

00:10:11.486 --> 00:10:12.606 A:middle
information shows up here.

00:10:12.606 --> 00:10:14.246 A:middle
So for example weather, calendar

00:10:14.246 --> 00:10:15.576 A:middle
and workouts, or maybe you'd

00:10:15.576 --> 00:10:16.826 A:middle
like to look at the date and

00:10:16.826 --> 00:10:18.326 A:middle
reminders and sunset.

00:10:18.326 --> 00:10:19.826 A:middle
The information that you like to

00:10:19.896 --> 00:10:21.016 A:middle
see actually varies based on

00:10:21.016 --> 00:10:22.546 A:middle
time and your location and your

00:10:22.546 --> 00:10:22.946 A:middle
routines.

00:10:23.706 --> 00:10:24.616 A:middle
What if we could actually show

00:10:24.616 --> 00:10:25.906 A:middle
you a selection of information

00:10:25.906 --> 00:10:26.606 A:middle
that you might need

00:10:26.836 --> 00:10:27.546 A:middle
automatically?

00:10:28.526 --> 00:10:29.876 A:middle
Well, Siri is becoming more and

00:10:29.876 --> 00:10:31.246 A:middle
more a proactive assistant

00:10:31.326 --> 00:10:32.386 A:middle
knowing what information you

00:10:32.386 --> 00:10:33.616 A:middle
need when you need it.

00:10:33.976 --> 00:10:35.246 A:middle
And we've created a new watch

00:10:35.246 --> 00:10:36.726 A:middle
face, which is powered by Siri

00:10:36.726 --> 00:10:37.326 A:middle
intelligence.

00:10:37.536 --> 00:10:39.086 A:middle
This is the new Siri watch face.

00:10:39.666 --> 00:10:40.906 A:middle
Now, it automatically displays

00:10:40.906 --> 00:10:41.966 A:middle
the information that's most

00:10:41.966 --> 00:10:42.716 A:middle
relevant to you.

00:10:42.716 --> 00:10:44.296 A:middle
And it can also access Siri by

00:10:44.296 --> 00:10:45.576 A:middle
tapping on the new complication

00:10:45.576 --> 00:10:46.256 A:middle
on the top left.

00:10:46.256 --> 00:10:48.146 A:middle
And it automatically displays

00:10:48.146 --> 00:10:49.496 A:middle
this information with the same

00:10:49.496 --> 00:10:50.626 A:middle
type of intelligence we've

00:10:50.626 --> 00:10:51.676 A:middle
applied on iOS.

00:10:52.116 --> 00:10:53.286 A:middle
We're using machine learning to

00:10:53.286 --> 00:10:54.606 A:middle
adapt automatically based on

00:10:54.606 --> 00:10:56.166 A:middle
your routines and the apps that

00:10:56.166 --> 00:10:57.366 A:middle
you use when you use them.

00:10:57.976 --> 00:10:59.016 A:middle
So in the morning, I might see

00:10:59.016 --> 00:11:01.166 A:middle
for example, can you time in my

00:11:01.166 --> 00:11:01.886 A:middle
first meeting.

00:11:01.966 --> 00:11:03.466 A:middle
And if I rotate the Crown, I can

00:11:03.466 --> 00:11:05.296 A:middle
see more information from Siri.

00:11:05.626 --> 00:11:07.086 A:middle
For example, reminders or even

00:11:07.086 --> 00:11:08.866 A:middle
photo memories from the same

00:11:08.866 --> 00:11:10.086 A:middle
time last year or maybe from

00:11:10.086 --> 00:11:10.836 A:middle
this location.

00:11:11.166 --> 00:11:12.136 A:middle
And throughout the day, whenever

00:11:12.136 --> 00:11:13.736 A:middle
you raise your wrist, the face

00:11:13.736 --> 00:11:14.996 A:middle
will dynamically update with the

00:11:14.996 --> 00:11:15.826 A:middle
information for you.

00:11:16.416 --> 00:11:17.736 A:middle
So for example at noon, I might

00:11:17.786 --> 00:11:19.146 A:middle
see a reminder to make a call

00:11:19.146 --> 00:11:20.466 A:middle
and I might get a pass to a

00:11:20.466 --> 00:11:21.316 A:middle
flight that I'm taking that

00:11:21.316 --> 00:11:21.926 A:middle
afternoon.

00:11:22.206 --> 00:11:23.576 A:middle
So, relevant passes in Wallet

00:11:23.576 --> 00:11:24.406 A:middle
can appear here right in the

00:11:24.406 --> 00:11:26.136 A:middle
face including from third party

00:11:26.136 --> 00:11:26.426 A:middle
apps.

00:11:26.426 --> 00:11:28.336 A:middle
Now, at the end of the day, I

