also use as a blinking safety

00:19:31.586 --> 00:19:32.346 A:middle
light when you're doing an

00:19:32.346 --> 00:19:32.996 A:middle
evening run.

00:19:33.046 --> 00:19:34.246 A:middle
So, a lot, lot more happening

00:19:34.246 --> 00:19:34.446 A:middle
here.

00:19:34.866 --> 00:19:36.076 A:middle
Now, we of course have a number

00:19:36.076 --> 00:19:37.936 A:middle
of updates that enable great

00:19:37.936 --> 00:19:40.006 A:middle
apps by developers in watchOS

00:19:40.006 --> 00:19:41.406 A:middle
including more support for apps

00:19:41.406 --> 00:19:42.306 A:middle
running in the background,

00:19:42.306 --> 00:19:44.076 A:middle
faster app responsiveness and

00:19:44.076 --> 00:19:45.416 A:middle
some new UI capabilities.

00:19:45.476 --> 00:19:46.986 A:middle
And we're also now supporting

00:19:46.986 --> 00:19:48.386 A:middle
native Core Bluetooth on the

00:19:48.386 --> 00:19:49.846 A:middle
watch, which is going to enable

00:19:49.846 --> 00:19:51.276 A:middle
experiences for apps that work

00:19:51.276 --> 00:19:52.836 A:middle
with small devices around you.

00:19:53.276 --> 00:19:54.816 A:middle
So for example, continuous

00:19:54.816 --> 00:19:56.216 A:middle
glucose monitoring, directly

