&gt;&gt; Thanks, Kevin.

00:20:32.016 --> 00:20:33.976 A:middle
[ Cheering Applause ]

00:20:33.976 --> 00:20:36.736 A:middle
WatchOS 4 is a great update.

00:20:37.796 --> 00:20:40.476 A:middle
Now, let's talk about a product

00:20:40.476 --> 00:20:43.506 A:middle
that in many ways is the heart

00:20:43.506 --> 00:20:44.796 A:middle
and soul of Apple.

00:20:45.526 --> 00:20:46.876 A:middle
And, of course, I'm talking

00:20:46.876 --> 00:20:48.256 A:middle
about the Mac.

00:20:49.516 --> 00:20:53.996 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:20:54.496 --> 00:20:56.026 A:middle
There's never been a computer

00:20:56.026 --> 00:20:56.876 A:middle
quite like the Mac.

00:20:58.246 --> 00:21:00.316 A:middle
The Mac is so important in

00:21:00.426 --> 00:21:02.556 A:middle
fueling the world's passion and

00:21:02.556 --> 00:21:03.266 A:middle
creativity.

00:21:03.866 --> 00:21:05.456 A:middle
It's a computer all of us love

00:21:05.456 --> 00:21:08.426 A:middle
to use and no one can match the

00:21:08.426 --> 00:21:10.586 A:middle
Mac's deep integration of

00:21:10.586 --> 00:21:12.036 A:middle
hardware and software.

00:21:13.106 --> 00:21:15.016 A:middle
And, of course, at the heart of

00:21:15.016 --> 00:21:18.016 A:middle
the Mac experience is macOS.

00:21:18.906 --> 00:21:20.186 A:middle
And to tell you about what's

00:21:20.186 --> 00:21:22.866 A:middle
next with macOS, please welcome

00:21:22.866 --> 00:21:24.606 A:middle
Craig Federighi, Craig.

00:21:25.506 --> 00:21:27.506 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:21:27.996 --> 00:21:28.526 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thank you.

00:21:28.756 --> 00:21:29.526 A:middle
Thank you, Tim.

00:21:30.246 --> 00:21:30.836 A:middle
Hey, good morning.

00:21:32.396 --> 00:21:34.576 A:middle
Well, let's talk about macOS.

00:21:35.216 --> 00:21:36.826 A:middle
Now, our current release of

00:21:36.826 --> 00:21:38.736 A:middle
macOS, of course, is macOS

00:21:38.836 --> 00:21:39.296 A:middle
Sierra.

00:21:39.696 --> 00:21:41.806 A:middle
Now, Sierra brought Siri and

00:21:41.806 --> 00:21:43.966 A:middle
Apple Pay to the Mac let you put

00:21:43.966 --> 00:21:45.626 A:middle
your documents and your desktop

00:21:45.626 --> 00:21:47.566 A:middle
in the cloud and even let you

00:21:47.566 --> 00:21:49.376 A:middle
unlock your Mac automatically

00:21:49.496 --> 00:21:51.476 A:middle
using the watch on your wrist.

00:21:52.386 --> 00:21:54.106 A:middle
Now, people are loving Sierra

00:21:54.106 --> 00:21:55.036 A:middle
and we love it too.

00:21:55.546 --> 00:21:57.096 A:middle
So, we wanted to spend this year

00:21:57.636 --> 00:21:58.496 A:middle
perfecting it.

00:21:59.206 --> 00:22:01.236 A:middle
Of course, the question is, what

00:22:01.236 --> 00:22:01.856 A:middle
do we call it?

00:22:02.016 --> 00:22:03.836 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:22:03.836 --> 00:22:05.646 A:middle
So we enlisted once again our

00:22:05.706 --> 00:22:07.256 A:middle
crack marketing team.

00:22:07.256 --> 00:22:08.706 A:middle
They were giddy to hop in their

00:22:08.706 --> 00:22:10.846 A:middle
mini bus and this time, venture

00:22:10.906 --> 00:22:13.576 A:middle
east, deep into the Sierras but

00:22:13.576 --> 00:22:16.146 A:middle
this time, ascending its highest

00:22:16.486 --> 00:22:16.966 A:middle
peaks.

00:22:17.346 --> 00:22:19.306 A:middle
And when they finally came back,

00:22:19.306 --> 00:22:20.786 A:middle
they had a name they said felt

00:22:21.176 --> 00:22:22.576 A:middle
really, really good.

00:22:22.576 --> 00:22:24.226 A:middle
And it's my privilege to

00:22:24.666 --> 00:22:26.966 A:middle
announce for you today, macOS

00:22:27.316 --> 00:22:28.366 A:middle
High Sierra.

00:22:29.516 --> 00:22:35.996 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:22:36.496 --> 00:22:38.656 A:middle
Now, we talked to the guys and

00:22:38.656 --> 00:22:40.066 A:middle
we said there might be-- this

00:22:40.066 --> 00:22:42.016 A:middle
might be misconstrued but they

00:22:42.016 --> 00:22:43.766 A:middle
assured us this name is fully

00:22:43.766 --> 00:22:44.166 A:middle
baked.

00:22:44.166 --> 00:22:44.266 A:middle
So--

00:22:45.016 --> 00:22:46.806 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:22:46.806 --> 00:22:49.446 A:middle
Now, High Sierra is all about

00:22:49.756 --> 00:22:51.926 A:middle
deep technologies that provide a

00:22:51.926 --> 00:22:53.426 A:middle
powerful platform for future

00:22:53.426 --> 00:22:54.766 A:middle
innovations on the Mac.

00:22:54.886 --> 00:22:56.986 A:middle
But we couldn't help ourselves,

00:22:56.986 --> 00:22:59.186 A:middle
we also added some refinements.

00:22:59.606 --> 00:23:01.186 A:middle
And it starts with Safari.

00:23:01.846 --> 00:23:03.556 A:middle
Now, Safari is known for its

00:23:03.556 --> 00:23:05.246 A:middle
efficiency and it's a legendary

00:23:05.246 --> 00:23:07.746 A:middle
battery life but safari is also

00:23:07.746 --> 00:23:09.176 A:middle
incredibly fast.

00:23:09.576 --> 00:23:11.666 A:middle
In fact, we benchmarked Safari

00:23:11.666 --> 00:23:13.466 A:middle
on the same hardware running

00:23:13.466 --> 00:23:15.616 A:middle
macOS and Windows with all the

00:23:15.616 --> 00:23:17.866 A:middle
popular browsers and Safari

00:23:17.926 --> 00:23:19.876 A:middle
smokes them in benchmark after

00:23:19.876 --> 00:23:21.386 A:middle
benchmark, JetStream,

00:23:21.386 --> 00:23:23.436 A:middle
Speedometer, MotionMark.

00:23:23.606 --> 00:23:25.266 A:middle
Safari tops them all.

00:23:25.686 --> 00:23:27.346 A:middle
That's right, Safari is the

00:23:27.346 --> 00:23:29.546 A:middle
world's fastest desktop browser

00:23:29.546 --> 00:23:30.286 A:middle
with High Sierra.

00:23:31.516 --> 00:23:33.796 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:23:34.296 --> 00:23:35.886 A:middle
And Safari's domination

00:23:35.886 --> 00:23:37.896 A:middle
continues with the new modern

00:23:37.896 --> 00:23:39.156 A:middle
version of JavaScript,

00:23:39.156 --> 00:23:40.586 A:middle
ECMAScript 5.

00:23:40.616 --> 00:23:43.516 A:middle
We can see Safari delivers 80%

00:23:43.516 --> 00:23:45.646 A:middle
faster performance than Chrome.

00:23:46.446 --> 00:23:47.586 A:middle
Now, in addition to being

00:23:47.586 --> 00:23:50.346 A:middle
tremendously fast, Safari also

00:23:50.346 --> 00:23:52.296 A:middle
helps give you a serene browsing

00:23:52.296 --> 00:23:53.076 A:middle
experience.

00:23:53.146 --> 00:23:54.416 A:middle
Now, you know, sometimes you go

00:23:54.416 --> 00:23:56.116 A:middle
to read an article and instead

00:23:56.116 --> 00:23:57.226 A:middle
of finding something to read,

00:23:57.226 --> 00:23:57.926 A:middle
you get this.

00:23:58.016 --> 00:23:59.766 A:middle
[ Music ]

00:23:59.766 --> 00:24:02.306 A:middle
Just some loud audio and video

00:24:02.306 --> 00:24:04.166 A:middle
that autoplays and disrupts your

00:24:04.166 --> 00:24:05.206 A:middle
whole reading vibe.

00:24:05.526 --> 00:24:07.896 A:middle
Well, now, don't worry about it

00:24:07.896 --> 00:24:09.346 A:middle
because we have autoplay

00:24:09.346 --> 00:24:10.916 A:middle
blocking in Safari.

00:24:11.516 --> 00:24:14.336 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:24:14.836 --> 00:24:16.936 A:middle
Safari detects the sites that

00:24:16.936 --> 00:24:18.496 A:middle
shouldn't be playing video and

00:24:18.496 --> 00:24:19.526 A:middle
puts you in control.

00:24:19.526 --> 00:24:20.996 A:middle
You can always push play.

00:24:21.596 --> 00:24:23.766 A:middle
Now, Safari is also key in

00:24:23.766 --> 00:24:25.606 A:middle
respecting your privacy.

00:24:25.996 --> 00:24:26.676 A:middle
Now, have you ever had this

00:24:26.676 --> 00:24:27.976 A:middle
experience where you go to buy

00:24:27.976 --> 00:24:29.416 A:middle
something on the web and you

00:24:29.416 --> 00:24:30.716 A:middle
even complete the purchase.

00:24:30.786 --> 00:24:32.986 A:middle
And it seems like everywhere you

00:24:32.986 --> 00:24:34.956 A:middle
go on the web, it just follows

00:24:34.956 --> 00:24:35.646 A:middle
you around.

00:24:36.706 --> 00:24:37.786 A:middle
It kind of feels like you're

00:24:37.786 --> 00:24:39.646 A:middle
being tracked and that's because

00:24:39.646 --> 00:24:39.976 A:middle
you are.

00:24:40.016 --> 00:24:41.846 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:24:41.846 --> 00:24:44.026 A:middle
No longer, because Safari has

00:24:44.076 --> 00:24:46.116 A:middle
Intelligent Tracking Prevention.

00:24:47.516 --> 00:24:51.746 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:24:52.246 --> 00:24:54.286 A:middle
Safari uses machine learning to

00:24:54.286 --> 00:24:56.806 A:middle
identify trackers, segregate the

00:24:56.806 --> 00:24:58.996 A:middle
cross-site scripting data, put

00:24:58.996 --> 00:25:01.676 A:middle
it away, so now, your privacy,

00:25:01.676 --> 00:25:02.956 A:middle
your browsing history is your

00:25:02.956 --> 00:25:03.146 A:middle
own.

00:25:03.316 --> 00:25:04.856 A:middle
It's not about blocking ads, the

00:25:04.856 --> 00:25:06.706 A:middle
web behaves as it always did,

00:25:06.816 --> 00:25:08.336 A:middle
but your privacy is protected.

00:25:09.216 --> 00:25:10.256 A:middle
Next, I want to talk about some

00:25:10.256 --> 00:25:11.726 A:middle
refinements to Mail and it

00:25:11.766 --> 00:25:12.866 A:middle
starts with search.

00:25:13.406 --> 00:25:14.346 A:middle
So in addition to providing

00:25:14.346 --> 00:25:16.156 A:middle
searches based on recency,

00:25:16.616 --> 00:25:18.486 A:middle
search in Mail is now using

00:25:18.486 --> 00:25:20.296 A:middle
Spotlight to identify your top

00:25:20.296 --> 00:25:20.526 A:middle
hits.

00:25:20.556 --> 00:25:21.536 A:middle
So the message you're looking

00:25:21.536 --> 00:25:23.246 A:middle
for is almost always right there

00:25:23.246 --> 00:25:24.356 A:middle
at the top.

00:25:24.496 --> 00:25:25.846 A:middle
And if you're into using Mail in

00:25:25.846 --> 00:25:27.216 A:middle
full-screen, well now, we

00:25:27.286 --> 00:25:29.116 A:middle
support Split View for your

00:25:29.116 --> 00:25:29.886 A:middle
compose window.

00:25:29.886 --> 00:25:31.796 A:middle
It's a great way to compose

00:25:31.796 --> 00:25:32.236 A:middle
mail.

00:25:33.516 --> 00:25:36.146 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:25:36.646 --> 00:25:37.856 A:middle
And Mail is more efficient than

00:25:37.856 --> 00:25:38.146 A:middle
ever.

00:25:38.146 --> 00:25:40.736 A:middle
It actually uses 35% less disk

00:25:40.736 --> 00:25:42.146 A:middle
space for storing your mail.

00:25:42.676 --> 00:25:44.596 A:middle
Now, probably our biggest area

00:25:44.596 --> 00:25:46.826 A:middle
of refinement in High Sierra is

00:25:46.826 --> 00:25:47.606 A:middle
in photos.

00:25:48.006 --> 00:25:49.976 A:middle
Now-- Yeah, photos has some

00:25:50.206 --> 00:25:51.666 A:middle
great new organization and

00:25:51.666 --> 00:25:52.276 A:middle
editing tools.

00:25:52.276 --> 00:25:54.446 A:middle
There's a persistent sidebar and

00:25:54.446 --> 00:25:56.226 A:middle
a new view that has all your

00:25:56.226 --> 00:25:58.436 A:middle
imports in chronological order.

00:25:58.436 --> 00:26:00.266 A:middle
And in any view up here on the

00:26:00.266 --> 00:26:02.606 A:middle
upper right, you can filter by

00:26:02.706 --> 00:26:04.556 A:middle
your keywords, by your

00:26:04.686 --> 00:26:06.996 A:middle
favorites, by just media types

00:26:06.996 --> 00:26:08.886 A:middle
like video so it's really easy

00:26:08.886 --> 00:26:09.846 A:middle
to get to just what you're

00:26:09.846 --> 00:26:10.616 A:middle
looking for.

00:26:11.306 --> 00:26:12.576 A:middle
We've also improved faces.

00:26:12.576 --> 00:26:14.246 A:middle
It recognizes far more faces

00:26:14.246 --> 00:26:16.506 A:middle
automatically using advanced

00:26:16.626 --> 00:26:18.016 A:middle
convolutional neural networks.

00:26:18.016 --> 00:26:19.916 A:middle
And when you put effort into

00:26:19.916 --> 00:26:21.586 A:middle
categorizing and naming people,

00:26:21.586 --> 00:26:23.106 A:middle
well, that's now synchronized

00:26:23.176 --> 00:26:24.686 A:middle
automatically across all your

00:26:24.686 --> 00:26:24.976 A:middle
devices.

00:26:25.516 --> 00:26:29.786 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:26:30.286 --> 00:26:31.486 A:middle
Now, we also have some great

00:26:31.486 --> 00:26:33.876 A:middle
enhancements to editing inside a

00:26:33.956 --> 00:26:34.246 A:middle
photo.

00:26:34.246 --> 00:26:35.156 A:middle
So you can see here on the

00:26:35.156 --> 00:26:37.446 A:middle
right-hand side, all of your

00:26:37.446 --> 00:26:38.496 A:middle
editing tools array.

00:26:38.496 --> 00:26:39.666 A:middle
And there are bunch of great new

00:26:39.666 --> 00:26:41.826 A:middle
ones, including Curves which

00:26:41.826 --> 00:26:43.636 A:middle
allows you to fine-tune the

00:26:43.636 --> 00:26:45.066 A:middle
color and contrast in your

00:26:45.066 --> 00:26:45.466 A:middle
image.

00:26:45.936 --> 00:26:47.616 A:middle
And Selective Color will teach

00:26:47.616 --> 00:26:49.076 A:middle
you modify color in a selective

00:26:49.076 --> 00:26:49.516 A:middle
range.

00:26:50.046 --> 00:26:50.876 A:middle
And I think you're going to like

00:26:50.876 --> 00:26:52.056 A:middle
this one because if you like to

00:26:52.566 --> 00:26:54.636 A:middle
do edits in a ProTool like

00:26:54.636 --> 00:26:56.496 A:middle
Pixelmator or Photoshop, well

00:26:56.496 --> 00:26:58.276 A:middle
now, when you punch out to that

00:26:58.276 --> 00:26:59.636 A:middle
other editing tool, all of your

00:26:59.636 --> 00:27:01.296 A:middle
edits automatically synchronize

00:27:01.296 --> 00:27:02.556 A:middle
right back to your photo

00:27:02.556 --> 00:27:02.976 A:middle
library.

00:27:03.516 --> 00:27:07.166 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:27:07.666 --> 00:27:10.516 A:middle
Now, Apple pioneered printed

00:27:10.516 --> 00:27:10.956 A:middle
books.

00:27:11.326 --> 00:27:13.216 A:middle
Based on projects, you construct

00:27:13.276 --> 00:27:15.116 A:middle
right inside of the photo

00:27:15.116 --> 00:27:15.836 A:middle
application.

00:27:16.026 --> 00:27:17.866 A:middle
And now, we're opening this up

00:27:17.866 --> 00:27:19.036 A:middle
to third parties.

00:27:19.456 --> 00:27:20.426 A:middle
They're going to offer some

00:27:20.426 --> 00:27:22.356 A:middle
amazing new printing services,

00:27:22.746 --> 00:27:25.046 A:middle
full-framed wall, mounted

00:27:25.046 --> 00:27:27.636 A:middle
photos, and even publishing

00:27:27.636 --> 00:27:29.516 A:middle
websites, all based on projects

00:27:29.596 --> 00:27:30.886 A:middle
right inside of photos.

00:27:31.466 --> 00:27:32.516 A:middle
So those are some quick

00:27:32.516 --> 00:27:33.896 A:middle
refinements but I want to return

00:27:33.896 --> 00:27:36.016 A:middle
to the main story now and that's

00:27:36.016 --> 00:27:37.456 A:middle
technology, this-- because we've

00:27:37.456 --> 00:27:38.946 A:middle
gone deep on the fundamentals,

00:27:39.506 --> 00:27:42.126 A:middle
data, video and graphics.

00:27:42.406 --> 00:27:44.266 A:middle
And when it comes to data, the

00:27:44.366 --> 00:27:46.226 A:middle
fundamentals are in the file

00:27:46.326 --> 00:27:46.736 A:middle
system.

00:27:47.266 --> 00:27:49.096 A:middle
Now, the Mac File System has its

00:27:49.096 --> 00:27:51.916 A:middle
roots actually, HFS from 30

00:27:52.016 --> 00:27:53.466 A:middle
years ago.

00:27:53.746 --> 00:27:55.086 A:middle
Well, a lot has changed since

00:27:55.116 --> 00:27:55.396 A:middle
then.

00:27:55.396 --> 00:27:56.976 A:middle
We have a lot of flash drives or

00:27:56.976 --> 00:27:58.506 A:middle
storage is a billion times

00:27:58.506 --> 00:28:00.646 A:middle
larger and it's time for more

00:28:00.646 --> 00:28:02.046 A:middle
modern file system.

00:28:02.646 --> 00:28:03.776 A:middle
So, I'm pleased to announce that

00:28:03.776 --> 00:28:05.326 A:middle
we're bringing the Apple File

00:28:05.416 --> 00:28:07.316 A:middle
System to macOS as our new

00:28:07.316 --> 00:28:07.646 A:middle
default.

00:28:08.516 --> 00:28:12.456 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:28:12.956 --> 00:28:15.276 A:middle
Now, APFS is a thoroughly modern

00:28:15.336 --> 00:28:17.536 A:middle
file system, 64-bit top to

00:28:17.536 --> 00:28:17.986 A:middle
bottom.

00:28:18.306 --> 00:28:19.796 A:middle
It's safe and secure with

00:28:19.796 --> 00:28:21.556 A:middle
built-in crash protection and

00:28:21.556 --> 00:28:22.836 A:middle
native encryption.

00:28:23.316 --> 00:28:25.236 A:middle
And it's ultra responsive with

00:28:25.236 --> 00:28:26.826 A:middle
modern features like instant

00:28:26.876 --> 00:28:28.926 A:middle
file and directory cloning and

00:28:28.926 --> 00:28:30.686 A:middle
high performance parallellized

00:28:30.686 --> 00:28:31.906 A:middle
metadata operations.

00:28:32.276 --> 00:28:33.276 A:middle
Now, what does that really mean

00:28:33.276 --> 00:28:34.016 A:middle
in practice?

00:28:34.356 --> 00:28:35.846 A:middle
Well, let's take a look at a

00:28:35.946 --> 00:28:38.076 A:middle
simple file duplication inside

00:28:38.076 --> 00:28:38.896 A:middle
of Sierra.

00:28:38.896 --> 00:28:40.346 A:middle
So we're going to go up to the

00:28:40.346 --> 00:28:40.956 A:middle
File menu.

00:28:41.276 --> 00:28:42.536 A:middle
It's like duplicate on this very

00:28:42.536 --> 00:28:43.556 A:middle
large video files.

00:28:43.556 --> 00:28:45.106 A:middle
And it's going to copy.

00:28:45.106 --> 00:28:45.826 A:middle
And just like you'd expect,

00:28:45.826 --> 00:28:46.786 A:middle
there's a lot of data to be

00:28:46.786 --> 00:28:48.396 A:middle
copied here so it takes a little

00:28:48.396 --> 00:28:51.326 A:middle
while, just about done, there we

00:28:51.326 --> 00:28:51.616 A:middle
go.

00:28:51.616 --> 00:28:54.006 A:middle
Now, let's watch that in High

00:28:54.006 --> 00:28:54.446 A:middle
Sierra.

00:28:54.526 --> 00:28:55.656 A:middle
Well, we're going to go up to

00:28:55.656 --> 00:28:56.886 A:middle
the File menu, we're going to

00:28:56.886 --> 00:28:58.976 A:middle
subduplicate, and we're done.

00:28:59.516 --> 00:29:04.436 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:29:04.936 --> 00:29:07.186 A:middle
Next up, video.

00:29:07.346 --> 00:29:08.936 A:middle
Now, the current standard in

00:29:08.936 --> 00:29:10.416 A:middle
video is H.264.

00:29:10.416 --> 00:29:12.366 A:middle
In fact, H.264 has really

00:29:12.366 --> 00:29:13.386 A:middle
enabled the revolution of

00:29:13.386 --> 00:29:15.266 A:middle
streaming HD video on the

00:29:15.266 --> 00:29:15.726 A:middle
Internet.

00:29:16.226 --> 00:29:17.046 A:middle
But, of course, the game is

00:29:17.046 --> 00:29:21.836 A:middle
moved from HD to 4K and 4K high

00:29:21.836 --> 00:29:23.406 A:middle
dynamic range video.

00:29:23.976 --> 00:29:25.486 A:middle
And there's a new standard to

00:29:25.486 --> 00:29:27.716 A:middle
support this, it's H.265 or

00:29:27.716 --> 00:29:28.096 A:middle
HEVC.

00:29:28.096 --> 00:29:30.566 A:middle
And you want your video to look

00:29:30.566 --> 00:29:32.956 A:middle
great, preserve all the detail

00:29:32.956 --> 00:29:34.946 A:middle
and color, and HEVC does it

00:29:35.606 --> 00:29:38.326 A:middle
while saving up to 40% better

00:29:38.326 --> 00:29:40.166 A:middle
compression than H.264.

00:29:40.166 --> 00:29:41.796 A:middle
Now, we're building in software

00:29:41.796 --> 00:29:42.836 A:middle
encoder support in the High

00:29:42.836 --> 00:29:45.476 A:middle
Sierra for all Macs and hardware

00:29:45.476 --> 00:29:48.356 A:middle
acceleration of HEVC for the

00:29:48.356 --> 00:29:49.266 A:middle
newest Macs.

00:29:49.446 --> 00:29:50.776 A:middle
And we're also building it into

00:29:50.776 --> 00:29:52.966 A:middle
ProTools, like Final Cut,

00:29:52.966 --> 00:29:54.686 A:middle
Motion, and Compressor.

00:29:55.566 --> 00:29:56.816 A:middle
Now, I want to return to our

00:29:56.816 --> 00:29:59.156 A:middle
main story which is graphics and

00:29:59.156 --> 00:30:01.536 A:middle
graphics are all about the GPU.

00:30:02.086 --> 00:30:03.536 A:middle
The GPU has been the performance

00:30:03.536 --> 00:30:05.766 A:middle
superstar of the last decade

00:30:06.066 --> 00:30:07.656 A:middle
delivering incredible gains in

00:30:07.656 --> 00:30:10.046 A:middle
computational performance.

00:30:10.046 --> 00:30:11.406 A:middle
Now, our API for

00:30:11.406 --> 00:30:13.056 A:middle
high-performance graphics is

00:30:13.056 --> 00:30:13.616 A:middle
Metal.

00:30:13.616 --> 00:30:15.016 A:middle
And developers have taken

00:30:15.016 --> 00:30:16.216 A:middle
amazing advantage of Metal.

00:30:16.216 --> 00:30:18.026 A:middle
This is Dawn of War III from

00:30:18.066 --> 00:30:19.536 A:middle
Feral Interactive, incredible

00:30:19.536 --> 00:30:20.106 A:middle
graphics.

00:30:20.856 --> 00:30:22.486 A:middle
This is DaVinci Resolve from

00:30:22.486 --> 00:30:24.626 A:middle
Blackmagic which can accelerate

00:30:24.626 --> 00:30:26.276 A:middle
many editing operations.

00:30:26.406 --> 00:30:27.686 A:middle
And, of course, we even use

00:30:27.686 --> 00:30:29.776 A:middle
Metal inside of photos for doing

00:30:29.776 --> 00:30:31.086 A:middle
machine learning in identifying

00:30:31.086 --> 00:30:31.706 A:middle
your photos.

00:30:32.226 --> 00:30:33.846 A:middle
But we've learned a lot working

00:30:33.846 --> 00:30:34.806 A:middle
with developers and their

00:30:34.806 --> 00:30:36.436 A:middle
adoption of Metal and we have a

00:30:36.436 --> 00:30:37.826 A:middle
new version to announce today.

00:30:37.826 --> 00:30:39.186 A:middle
And you'll never guess what we

00:30:39.186 --> 00:30:39.636 A:middle
called it.

00:30:40.496 --> 00:30:40.976 A:middle
It's Metal 2.

00:30:41.016 --> 00:30:42.966 A:middle
[ Laughter ]

00:30:42.966 --> 00:30:45.806 A:middle
Now, Metal 2 is tremendously

00:30:45.806 --> 00:30:46.326 A:middle
fast.

00:30:46.326 --> 00:30:47.596 A:middle
In fact, it has great

00:30:47.596 --> 00:30:49.456 A:middle
optimizations and new APIs that

00:30:49.456 --> 00:30:52.146 A:middle
when adopted, deliver another 10

00:30:52.146 --> 00:30:54.076 A:middle
times improvement in draw call

00:30:54.076 --> 00:30:54.676 A:middle
throughput.

00:30:54.846 --> 00:30:55.726 A:middle
Now, some of you remember when

00:30:55.726 --> 00:30:57.466 A:middle
Metal first came out, it itself

00:30:57.466 --> 00:30:58.746 A:middle
had a 10 times improvement over

00:30:58.746 --> 00:30:59.286 A:middle
OpenGL.

00:30:59.566 --> 00:31:00.736 A:middle
You can multiply those numbers

00:31:00.736 --> 00:31:01.096 A:middle
together.

00:31:01.096 --> 00:31:02.396 A:middle
That's a hundred times

00:31:02.396 --> 00:31:03.016 A:middle
improvement.

00:31:03.446 --> 00:31:05.216 A:middle
Now, we've also provided

00:31:05.416 --> 00:31:09.366 A:middle
better-- sorry, debugging and

00:31:09.416 --> 00:31:11.066 A:middle
performance analysis tools for

00:31:11.066 --> 00:31:12.096 A:middle
you to optimize your app for

00:31:12.096 --> 00:31:12.406 A:middle
Metal.

00:31:12.406 --> 00:31:14.176 A:middle
And we're so excited about the

00:31:14.176 --> 00:31:16.086 A:middle
advances in Metal 2 that we've

00:31:16.086 --> 00:31:18.326 A:middle
taken the Mac Window Server and

00:31:18.326 --> 00:31:19.796 A:middle
put it on top of Metal,

00:31:19.796 --> 00:31:21.666 A:middle
accelerating things like Mission

00:31:21.666 --> 00:31:22.296 A:middle
Control.

00:31:22.296 --> 00:31:23.616 A:middle
And some of our most challenging

00:31:23.616 --> 00:31:24.846 A:middle
system animations are now

00:31:24.966 --> 00:31:27.026 A:middle
buttery smooth all the time.

00:31:27.456 --> 00:31:29.546 A:middle
Now, Metal is not just about

00:31:29.546 --> 00:31:30.146 A:middle
graphics.

00:31:30.146 --> 00:31:32.246 A:middle
We're also using it for machine

00:31:32.246 --> 00:31:32.836 A:middle
learning.

00:31:32.836 --> 00:31:34.946 A:middle
It can now accelerate-- yes, we

00:31:34.946 --> 00:31:36.636 A:middle
have Metal performance shaders

00:31:36.856 --> 00:31:38.836 A:middle
to accelerate all kinds of deep

00:31:38.836 --> 00:31:39.916 A:middle
learning algorithms.

00:31:40.766 --> 00:31:41.866 A:middle
Another piece of Metal news

00:31:41.916 --> 00:31:44.216 A:middle
today is Metal for external

00:31:44.216 --> 00:31:44.936 A:middle
graphics.

00:31:45.966 --> 00:31:48.266 A:middle
So, you know our MacBooks have

00:31:48.266 --> 00:31:50.146 A:middle
this tremendous balance of

00:31:50.196 --> 00:31:52.026 A:middle
portability and power.

00:31:52.846 --> 00:31:54.106 A:middle
But sometimes for some

00:31:54.106 --> 00:31:56.006 A:middle
workflows, you need even more

00:31:56.006 --> 00:31:56.246 A:middle
power.

00:31:56.246 --> 00:31:57.706 A:middle
You want to take advantage of

00:31:57.706 --> 00:32:00.366 A:middle
the incredible Thunderbolt IO on

00:32:00.366 --> 00:32:02.556 A:middle
your MacBook Pros to access

00:32:02.556 --> 00:32:04.046 A:middle
external graphics.

00:32:04.996 --> 00:32:05.966 A:middle
So we're going to be making this

00:32:05.996 --> 00:32:07.186 A:middle
possible in Metal 2.

00:32:07.606 --> 00:32:09.416 A:middle
Now, we're starting with the

00:32:09.416 --> 00:32:10.376 A:middle
Developer Kit that will be

00:32:10.376 --> 00:32:11.316 A:middle
available today.

00:32:11.316 --> 00:32:13.296 A:middle
You can actually order a

00:32:13.296 --> 00:32:14.746 A:middle
Thunderbolt 3 enclosure with a

00:32:14.746 --> 00:32:17.956 A:middle
high-performance AMD GPU and

00:32:17.956 --> 00:32:19.616 A:middle
tune your apps for

00:32:19.616 --> 00:32:20.866 A:middle
high-performance external

00:32:20.866 --> 00:32:21.356 A:middle
graphics.

00:32:21.496 --> 00:32:22.766 A:middle
And then we'll be rolling out

00:32:22.816 --> 00:32:24.716 A:middle
support to all of our customers

00:32:25.116 --> 00:32:26.046 A:middle
in the months to come.

00:32:27.446 --> 00:32:29.216 A:middle
Now, with these graphics power,

00:32:29.486 --> 00:32:30.716 A:middle
we're really doubling down on

00:32:30.716 --> 00:32:31.996 A:middle
our focus on Pro content

00:32:31.996 --> 00:32:32.536 A:middle
creation.

00:32:33.136 --> 00:32:34.756 A:middle
And that's increasingly about VR

00:32:34.756 --> 00:32:36.896 A:middle
content creation.

00:32:37.406 --> 00:32:40.666 A:middle
And so, we're bringing Metal for

00:32:41.006 --> 00:32:41.766 A:middle
VR to High Sierra.

00:32:42.516 --> 00:32:46.096 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:32:46.596 --> 00:32:47.686 A:middle
Now Metal is delivering a

00:32:47.806 --> 00:32:50.526 A:middle
VR-optimized display pipeline

00:32:50.526 --> 00:32:51.806 A:middle
that provides extremely high

00:32:51.806 --> 00:32:52.626 A:middle
performance.

00:32:53.166 --> 00:32:55.196 A:middle
And we're optimizing our Pro

00:32:55.196 --> 00:32:56.406 A:middle
apps like Final Cut for doing

00:32:56.406 --> 00:32:57.536 A:middle
things like editing spherical

00:32:57.536 --> 00:32:59.136 A:middle
video right inside the VR

00:32:59.136 --> 00:32:59.626 A:middle
environment.

00:33:00.176 --> 00:33:01.946 A:middle
We're also working with Valve.

00:33:01.946 --> 00:33:03.476 A:middle
They're bringing the SteamVR,

00:33:03.476 --> 00:33:04.236 A:middle
SVK to the Mac.

00:33:04.886 --> 00:33:07.896 A:middle
And we work with Unity and

00:33:07.896 --> 00:33:09.676 A:middle
Unreal to bring their engines

00:33:09.916 --> 00:33:11.276 A:middle
for VR to the Mac.

00:33:12.516 --> 00:33:16.396 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

00:33:16.896 --> 00:33:18.086 A:middle
It's really cool and you might

00:33:18.126 --> 00:33:19.356 A:middle
just be seeing a little bit more

00:33:19.356 --> 00:33:20.796 A:middle
from us later today on this

00:33:20.796 --> 00:33:21.266 A:middle
topic.

00:33:21.686 --> 00:33:24.146 A:middle
So that's a quick look at macOS.

00:33:24.176 --> 00:33:25.926 A:middle
Some great technologies with the

00:33:25.926 --> 00:33:28.956 A:middle
Apple File System, HEVC Video

00:33:29.046 --> 00:33:30.966 A:middle
and incredible graphics with

00:33:30.966 --> 00:33:33.306 A:middle
Metal 2 support for external

00:33:33.306 --> 00:33:35.286 A:middle
graphics and VR support of the

00:33:35.286 --> 00:33:37.436 A:middle
Mac and, of course, a bunch of

00:33:37.496 --> 00:33:38.886 A:middle
fantastic refinements.

