&gt;&gt; Thank you, Craig.

00:34:17.616 --> 00:34:19.686 A:middle
So, we have some great updates

00:34:19.726 --> 00:34:21.176 A:middle
to talk about today that span

00:34:21.176 --> 00:34:22.666 A:middle
much of the Mac product line.

00:34:23.036 --> 00:34:24.346 A:middle
And let's begin with the iMac.

00:34:25.636 --> 00:34:27.246 A:middle
Now, the iMac has been the gold

00:34:27.246 --> 00:34:28.786 A:middle
standard of desktops for many

00:34:28.786 --> 00:34:30.076 A:middle
years but we're going to raise

00:34:30.076 --> 00:34:31.316 A:middle
the bar once again.

00:34:31.816 --> 00:34:33.316 A:middle
And as always on the iMac, it

00:34:33.316 --> 00:34:34.496 A:middle
starts with the display.

00:34:35.486 --> 00:34:37.276 A:middle
Because the 4K and 5K Retina

00:34:37.456 --> 00:34:38.836 A:middle
iMac displays with their high

00:34:38.836 --> 00:34:40.626 A:middle
resolution, excellent brightness

00:34:40.786 --> 00:34:42.796 A:middle
and P3 color gamut, are the best

00:34:42.796 --> 00:34:44.286 A:middle
displays on any desktop.

00:34:44.286 --> 00:34:45.706 A:middle
But we're going to make them

00:34:45.706 --> 00:34:46.276 A:middle
even better.

00:34:46.986 --> 00:34:48.776 A:middle
So these new displays are now

00:34:48.776 --> 00:34:50.336 A:middle
going to be 500 nits.

00:34:50.376 --> 00:34:52.276 A:middle
That's 43% brighter than the

00:34:52.276 --> 00:34:53.196 A:middle
previous generation.

00:34:53.806 --> 00:34:55.456 A:middle
And for the first time, we're

00:34:55.456 --> 00:34:56.546 A:middle
going to support 10-bit

00:34:56.546 --> 00:34:57.856 A:middle
dithering, which means these

00:34:57.856 --> 00:34:59.206 A:middle
displays can reproduce up to a

00:34:59.206 --> 00:35:00.416 A:middle
billion colors.

00:35:01.586 --> 00:35:02.776 A:middle
So, your content is going to

00:35:02.776 --> 00:35:04.236 A:middle
look more true to life than ever

00:35:04.236 --> 00:35:04.666 A:middle
before.

00:35:05.566 --> 00:35:06.976 A:middle
Now, in addition, we've got some

00:35:06.976 --> 00:35:08.456 A:middle
great internal updates for these

00:35:08.546 --> 00:35:08.906 A:middle
iMacs.

00:35:09.286 --> 00:35:10.496 A:middle
So we'll start with the CPU

00:35:10.496 --> 00:35:11.826 A:middle
because the whole line is moving

00:35:11.826 --> 00:35:13.666 A:middle
to Intel's 7th-generation Core

00:35:13.666 --> 00:35:15.546 A:middle
Processor, also known as Kaby

00:35:15.546 --> 00:35:15.776 A:middle
Lake.

00:35:16.166 --> 00:35:17.486 A:middle
Now, Kaby Lake gets this better

00:35:17.486 --> 00:35:19.216 A:middle
base and turbo frequencies for

00:35:19.216 --> 00:35:20.856 A:middle
more performance as well as

00:35:20.856 --> 00:35:23.166 A:middle
hardware-based 10-bit HEVC

00:35:23.166 --> 00:35:24.586 A:middle
decode which is great for

00:35:24.586 --> 00:35:25.966 A:middle
playing back high quality video.

00:35:27.016 --> 00:35:28.316 A:middle
In addition, these iMacs are

00:35:28.316 --> 00:35:29.396 A:middle
getting a boost when it comes to

00:35:29.396 --> 00:35:30.366 A:middle
memory capacity.

