understands your voice, it

00:57:45.086 --> 00:57:46.796 A:middle
understands the context.

00:57:47.116 --> 00:57:49.006 A:middle
It understands your interest.

00:57:49.236 --> 00:57:50.426 A:middle
It understands how you use your

00:57:50.426 --> 00:57:50.906 A:middle
device.

00:57:50.906 --> 00:57:53.146 A:middle
And this allows it to ultimately

00:57:53.146 --> 00:57:55.296 A:middle
understand what you want next.

00:57:55.886 --> 00:57:57.726 A:middle
Now, we've all experienced this

00:57:57.726 --> 00:57:58.926 A:middle
where Siri can help us predict

00:57:59.306 --> 00:58:00.746 A:middle
what apps we might want to use

00:58:00.746 --> 00:58:03.136 A:middle
next, give us a time to leave

00:58:03.136 --> 00:58:04.316 A:middle
notification based on our

00:58:04.316 --> 00:58:06.976 A:middle
calendar and where we are, help

00:58:06.976 --> 00:58:08.456 A:middle
us respond to a text message.

00:58:08.976 --> 00:58:11.636 A:middle
In iOS 11, Siri uses on-device

00:58:11.636 --> 00:58:13.096 A:middle
learning to understand more

00:58:13.096 --> 00:58:14.816 A:middle
about topics of interest to us.

00:58:15.266 --> 00:58:16.636 A:middle
So it can actually suggest

00:58:16.636 --> 00:58:18.626 A:middle
topics we might be interested in

00:58:18.626 --> 00:58:19.716 A:middle
learning about in news.

00:58:19.716 --> 00:58:22.116 A:middle
It can help us respond with our

00:58:22.116 --> 00:58:23.396 A:middle
location for getting to an

00:58:23.396 --> 00:58:25.046 A:middle
appointment to someone in

00:58:25.046 --> 00:58:25.686 A:middle
messages.

