your next move when navigating.

01:08:47.516 --> 01:08:49.706 A:middle
[ Applause ]

01:08:50.206 --> 01:08:51.596 A:middle
Now, we know in addition to

01:08:51.596 --> 01:08:52.766 A:middle
navigation, people like to do

01:08:52.766 --> 01:08:54.716 A:middle
more with their phones sometimes

01:08:54.716 --> 01:08:55.246 A:middle
while driving.

01:08:55.386 --> 01:08:57.226 A:middle
And our safest solution for

01:08:57.226 --> 01:08:59.286 A:middle
doing this is CarPlay, lets you

01:08:59.286 --> 01:09:00.996 A:middle
keep your eyes on the road while

01:09:00.996 --> 01:09:02.246 A:middle
you're doing things like asking

01:09:02.246 --> 01:09:03.926 A:middle
Siri to play music.

01:09:03.926 --> 01:09:05.376 A:middle
Well, we wanted to bring this

01:09:05.376 --> 01:09:07.916 A:middle
same level of safety to everyone

01:09:07.916 --> 01:09:09.146 A:middle
who maybe doesn't have one of

01:09:09.146 --> 01:09:11.576 A:middle
the 200 models of cars that

01:09:11.576 --> 01:09:12.976 A:middle
currently support CarPlay.

01:09:12.976 --> 01:09:15.046 A:middle
And we're building on "Do Not

01:09:15.046 --> 01:09:16.646 A:middle
Disturb" with a new feature we

01:09:16.646 --> 01:09:18.566 A:middle
call "Do Not Disturb While

01:09:18.566 --> 01:09:19.036 A:middle
Driving".

01:09:19.036 --> 01:09:21.506 A:middle
And it's all about keeping your

01:09:21.506 --> 01:09:22.396 A:middle
eyes on the road.

01:09:22.396 --> 01:09:23.896 A:middle
When you're driving, you don't

01:09:23.896 --> 01:09:26.016 A:middle
need to be responding to these

01:09:26.016 --> 01:09:27.586 A:middle
kinds of messages.

01:09:27.586 --> 01:09:28.626 A:middle
In fact, you don't need to see

01:09:28.626 --> 01:09:28.846 A:middle
them.

01:09:29.856 --> 01:09:33.816 A:middle
So now, when you install iOS 11,

01:09:34.256 --> 01:09:35.576 A:middle
we're going to use Bluetooth to

01:09:35.576 --> 01:09:36.676 A:middle
understand if you're connected

01:09:36.676 --> 01:09:36.896 A:middle
to a car.

