[ Applause and Cheering ]

01:10:45.746 --> 01:10:47.516 A:middle
Next up, HomeKit.

01:10:47.806 --> 01:10:50.606 A:middle
So HomeKit provides a secure and

01:10:50.716 --> 01:10:53.126 A:middle
private way to automate all of

01:10:53.126 --> 01:10:55.006 A:middle
your devices, your home

01:10:55.006 --> 01:10:56.796 A:middle
accessories and you can do it

01:10:56.796 --> 01:10:58.376 A:middle
right inside the home map and

01:10:58.376 --> 01:10:59.096 A:middle
control them here.

01:10:59.096 --> 01:11:00.146 A:middle
And also, of course, use your

01:11:00.146 --> 01:11:01.216 A:middle
voice with Siri.

01:11:01.736 --> 01:11:03.006 A:middle
Now, almost all of the major

01:11:03.006 --> 01:11:04.356 A:middle
accessory makers are providing

01:11:04.606 --> 01:11:06.186 A:middle
great HomeKit accessories across

01:11:06.596 --> 01:11:08.396 A:middle
all of these categories, from

01:11:08.396 --> 01:11:10.546 A:middle
security cameras and door locks

01:11:10.546 --> 01:11:11.936 A:middle
to lights and fans.

01:11:12.626 --> 01:11:14.266 A:middle
But there's one category really

01:11:14.266 --> 01:11:15.436 A:middle
close to our heart that we

01:11:15.436 --> 01:11:16.836 A:middle
wanted to add to HomeKit.

01:11:16.836 --> 01:11:19.146 A:middle
And that's Speakers.

01:11:20.516 --> 01:11:22.846 A:middle
[ Applause ]

01:11:23.346 --> 01:11:24.636 A:middle
You'll now be able to configure

01:11:24.636 --> 01:11:26.216 A:middle
your speakers inside of HomeKit

01:11:26.216 --> 01:11:29.136 A:middle
and access them via our new

01:11:29.136 --> 01:11:30.746 A:middle
AirPlay 2 protocol.

01:11:31.076 --> 01:11:34.016 A:middle
It builds multi-room audio in

01:11:34.126 --> 01:11:34.846 A:middle
throughout iOS.

01:11:35.516 --> 01:11:39.926 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

01:11:40.426 --> 01:11:41.986 A:middle
So, you can play music to select

01:11:41.986 --> 01:11:43.626 A:middle
speakers throughout your home

01:11:43.936 --> 01:11:45.116 A:middle
right from the Music app.

01:11:45.436 --> 01:11:46.986 A:middle
And with Apple Music, we have a

01:11:46.986 --> 01:11:48.046 A:middle
new feature called Shared Up

01:11:48.046 --> 01:11:48.286 A:middle
Next.

01:11:48.636 --> 01:11:49.806 A:middle
So if you have a friend over and

01:11:49.806 --> 01:11:51.426 A:middle
you have a playlist going and

01:11:51.426 --> 01:11:52.176 A:middle
maybe your friend wants to

01:11:52.176 --> 01:11:53.376 A:middle
contribute to that playlist,

01:11:53.416 --> 01:11:55.216 A:middle
well they can do that without

01:11:55.216 --> 01:11:56.246 A:middle
interrupting the music.

01:11:56.246 --> 01:11:57.856 A:middle
You all compile into that party

01:11:57.936 --> 01:11:58.496 A:middle
playlist.

01:11:59.096 --> 01:12:00.726 A:middle
Now, the-- all these speaker

01:12:00.726 --> 01:12:02.246 A:middle
makers have announced upcoming

01:12:02.246 --> 01:12:04.706 A:middle
support for AirPlay 2, but, of

01:12:04.706 --> 01:12:07.006 A:middle
course, many of us already own a

01:12:07.006 --> 01:12:08.746 A:middle
great AirPlay 2 compatible

01:12:08.746 --> 01:12:09.686 A:middle
speaker and those are the ones

01:12:09.686 --> 01:12:11.526 A:middle
connected to our Apple TV.

01:12:11.846 --> 01:12:13.996 A:middle
Because now, your Apple TV can

01:12:13.996 --> 01:12:16.546 A:middle
be played to from your iPhone or

01:12:16.546 --> 01:12:17.936 A:middle
iOS device in Mac anywhere in

01:12:17.936 --> 01:12:18.346 A:middle
the home.

01:12:18.696 --> 01:12:19.976 A:middle
And, of course, if you turn on

01:12:19.976 --> 01:12:21.676 A:middle
your Apple TV, it can control

01:12:21.676 --> 01:12:24.716 A:middle
playback homewide including

01:12:24.716 --> 01:12:26.016 A:middle
using Siri.

01:12:26.436 --> 01:12:27.906 A:middle
And we're providing a great

01:12:27.906 --> 01:12:29.816 A:middle
developer API, so third party

01:12:29.816 --> 01:12:31.486 A:middle
audio apps in iOS can all get in

01:12:31.486 --> 01:12:33.346 A:middle
on the multi-room audio fun.

01:12:34.436 --> 01:12:36.096 A:middle
Next is Apple Music.

01:12:37.016 --> 01:12:39.546 A:middle
Now, last fall, we introduced

01:12:39.546 --> 01:12:40.966 A:middle
the all new design for Apple

01:12:40.966 --> 01:12:42.166 A:middle
Music which brought greater

01:12:42.166 --> 01:12:43.886 A:middle
clarity and simplicity to the

01:12:43.886 --> 01:12:45.266 A:middle
Apple Music experience.

01:12:46.416 --> 01:12:48.626 A:middle
We now have 27 million customers

01:12:48.626 --> 01:12:49.796 A:middle
who are really enjoying the

01:12:49.796 --> 01:12:51.516 A:middle
curation as well as the

01:12:51.516 --> 01:12:53.736 A:middle
personalization of Apple Music.

01:12:53.736 --> 01:12:54.846 A:middle
But, of course, a lot of the way

01:12:54.846 --> 01:12:56.196 A:middle
we discover music is to ask one

01:12:56.196 --> 01:12:57.616 A:middle
of our friends, "What have you

01:12:57.616 --> 01:12:58.846 A:middle
been listening to lately?"

01:12:59.256 --> 01:13:01.266 A:middle
So now, in Apple Music, you'll

01:13:01.266 --> 01:13:03.726 A:middle
be able to find out right inside

01:13:03.726 --> 01:13:04.576 A:middle
the application.

01:13:05.516 --> 01:13:07.596 A:middle
[ Applause ]

01:13:08.096 --> 01:13:10.856 A:middle
For all the music served up and

01:13:10.856 --> 01:13:12.456 A:middle
for you, you'll see indicators

01:13:12.456 --> 01:13:13.416 A:middle
if this is the music your

01:13:13.486 --> 01:13:15.256 A:middle
friends are listening to and

01:13:15.256 --> 01:13:17.096 A:middle
they can configure their profile

01:13:17.446 --> 01:13:19.246 A:middle
either to be public or private

01:13:19.246 --> 01:13:20.556 A:middle
and control what playlists they

01:13:20.556 --> 01:13:21.806 A:middle
share or what are all the music

01:13:21.806 --> 01:13:22.806 A:middle
they share they want to make

01:13:22.806 --> 01:13:23.516 A:middle
available to their other

01:13:23.586 --> 01:13:24.026 A:middle
friends.

01:13:24.536 --> 01:13:26.016 A:middle
Now for developers, we're also

01:13:26.016 --> 01:13:28.166 A:middle
providing a new API MusicKit for

01:13:28.166 --> 01:13:28.746 A:middle
Apple Music.

01:13:29.236 --> 01:13:31.826 A:middle
This allows apps full access to

01:13:31.826 --> 01:13:33.856 A:middle
the Apple Music service, both on

01:13:33.856 --> 01:13:34.946 A:middle
device and from your cloud

01:13:34.946 --> 01:13:35.506 A:middle
service.

01:13:36.226 --> 01:13:37.496 A:middle
And you can do a tremendous

01:13:37.496 --> 01:13:38.146 A:middle
amount with this.

01:13:38.146 --> 01:13:39.756 A:middle
Now, Nike has done great

01:13:39.756 --> 01:13:41.326 A:middle
exercise playlists using the

01:13:41.326 --> 01:13:42.676 A:middle
full Apple Music catalog.

01:13:43.006 --> 01:13:44.936 A:middle
With Anchor, anyone can be a DJ

01:13:44.936 --> 01:13:46.896 A:middle
using all 40 million songs.

01:13:47.206 --> 01:13:49.726 A:middle
And Shazam can automatically add

01:13:49.816 --> 01:13:51.396 A:middle
songs to your collection that it

01:13:51.396 --> 01:13:52.156 A:middle
identifies.

01:13:52.896 --> 01:13:53.576 A:middle
But, you know, one of the

01:13:53.576 --> 01:13:56.746 A:middle
biggest stories today for iOS 11

01:13:57.506 --> 01:13:59.516 A:middle
is about the App Store.

01:14:00.346 --> 01:14:02.566 A:middle
Now, to give you the big news

01:14:02.726 --> 01:14:04.166 A:middle
with the App Store, I'd like to

01:14:04.166 --> 01:14:06.436 A:middle
hand it off to Phil Schiller.

01:14:06.436 --> 01:14:07.186 A:middle
Thank you.

01:14:08.401 --> 01:14:10.401 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

01:14:10.786 --> 01:14:11.326 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Thank you, Craig.

01:14:14.936 --> 01:14:15.946 A:middle
Well, good morning everyone.

01:14:16.236 --> 01:14:17.896 A:middle
Let's hear it from the way back

01:14:17.896 --> 01:14:18.336 A:middle
of the room.

01:14:18.336 --> 01:14:19.736 A:middle
Come on. Good morning, everyone.

01:14:20.016 --> 01:14:21.046 A:middle
[ Cheering ]

01:14:21.046 --> 01:14:25.676 A:middle
Yes. I am so excited to be able

01:14:25.676 --> 01:14:26.976 A:middle
to talk to you this morning

01:14:27.036 --> 01:14:28.386 A:middle
about the App Store.

01:14:28.656 --> 01:14:29.966 A:middle
The App Store is turning nine

01:14:29.966 --> 01:14:31.866 A:middle
years old and it is going so

01:14:31.866 --> 01:14:32.296 A:middle
well.

01:14:32.296 --> 01:14:36.586 A:middle
There are 500 million weekly

01:14:36.586 --> 01:14:38.246 A:middle
visitors to the App Store who

01:14:38.296 --> 01:14:40.816 A:middle
come to see your amazing apps

01:14:41.026 --> 01:14:41.936 A:middle
and to download them.

01:14:41.936 --> 01:14:43.666 A:middle
They have now downloaded over

01:14:43.666 --> 01:14:47.416 A:middle
180 billion apps to date.

01:14:47.896 --> 01:14:48.776 A:middle
That's incredible.

01:14:49.056 --> 01:14:50.846 A:middle
That does not include auto

01:14:50.846 --> 01:14:52.756 A:middle
re-downloads and updates.

01:14:53.296 --> 01:14:55.726 A:middle
Amazing. And just recently, we

01:14:55.726 --> 01:14:59.216 A:middle
passed $70 billion paid out to

01:14:59.216 --> 01:14:59.976 A:middle
developers today.

01:15:00.516 --> 01:15:02.816 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

01:15:03.316 --> 01:15:05.836 A:middle
Yes. Thirty percent of that in

01:15:05.836 --> 01:15:09.096 A:middle
the last year alone, the apps

01:15:09.096 --> 01:15:09.826 A:middle
are incredible.

01:15:09.826 --> 01:15:11.166 A:middle
And customers are doing things

01:15:11.166 --> 01:15:12.076 A:middle
with them that none of us have

01:15:12.076 --> 01:15:13.296 A:middle
ever imagined.

01:15:13.776 --> 01:15:14.246 A:middle
Like this.

01:15:15.206 --> 01:15:17.496 A:middle
These are people in Hong Kong

01:15:17.496 --> 01:15:18.866 A:middle
playing Pokemon Go.

01:15:21.456 --> 01:15:22.876 A:middle
Pokemon Go is from Niantic.

01:15:22.876 --> 01:15:24.066 A:middle
It was one of the big hits from

01:15:24.066 --> 01:15:24.826 A:middle
last year and there have been a

01:15:24.826 --> 01:15:26.216 A:middle
lot of big hits last year from

01:15:26.216 --> 01:15:27.286 A:middle
big developers and indie

01:15:27.286 --> 01:15:28.116 A:middle
developers alike.

01:15:28.116 --> 01:15:30.436 A:middle
And together, the developers at

01:15:30.436 --> 01:15:32.436 A:middle
Apple, we've made this the best

01:15:32.436 --> 01:15:34.096 A:middle
app platform in the world.

01:15:34.096 --> 01:15:34.976 A:middle
So thank you.

01:15:35.516 --> 01:15:38.396 A:middle
[ Applause ]

01:15:38.896 --> 01:15:40.816 A:middle
Yes. Thank you for the

01:15:40.816 --> 01:15:42.566 A:middle
incredible apps you make that we

01:15:42.566 --> 01:15:43.796 A:middle
and our customers all love.

01:15:44.346 --> 01:15:45.976 A:middle
It's not by chance that the App

01:15:45.976 --> 01:15:47.076 A:middle
Store has become such a great

01:15:47.076 --> 01:15:47.516 A:middle
place.

01:15:47.766 --> 01:15:48.766 A:middle
From the beginning, we've had

01:15:48.766 --> 01:15:50.916 A:middle
two very important goals, to

01:15:50.916 --> 01:15:52.556 A:middle
make the App Store a trusted and

01:15:52.556 --> 01:15:55.056 A:middle
safe place for users and to make

01:15:55.056 --> 01:15:57.436 A:middle
it a great opportunity for all

01:15:57.436 --> 01:15:58.206 A:middle
developers.

01:15:58.516 --> 01:16:00.066 A:middle
We continue to work really hard

01:16:00.066 --> 01:16:00.356 A:middle
at that.

01:16:00.356 --> 01:16:02.136 A:middle
Over the last year, the team has

01:16:02.136 --> 01:16:03.526 A:middle
done a lot of great things to

01:16:03.526 --> 01:16:04.966 A:middle
make the App Store an even

01:16:04.966 --> 01:16:06.656 A:middle
better store for all of us.

01:16:06.986 --> 01:16:08.116 A:middle
There's many things we can talk

01:16:08.116 --> 01:16:09.566 A:middle
about but I think one stands

01:16:09.566 --> 01:16:10.446 A:middle
head and shoulders above the

01:16:10.446 --> 01:16:12.906 A:middle
rest, faster app review times.

01:16:13.016 --> 01:16:14.066 A:middle
[ Applause ]

01:16:14.066 --> 01:16:18.746 A:middle
Yes. I'm sure you're well aware

01:16:19.056 --> 01:16:20.116 A:middle
that the majority of apps are

01:16:20.116 --> 01:16:22.116 A:middle
all now reviewed in under 24

01:16:22.116 --> 01:16:23.986 A:middle
hours, many in just one to two

01:16:23.986 --> 01:16:24.456 A:middle
hours.

01:16:24.716 --> 01:16:25.496 A:middle
The team is going to keep

01:16:25.496 --> 01:16:26.386 A:middle
working hard at that.

01:16:26.576 --> 01:16:28.456 A:middle
And we have a lot more coming

01:16:28.456 --> 01:16:29.976 A:middle
for the remainder of the year.

01:16:29.976 --> 01:16:31.066 A:middle
I've highlighted a bunch of

01:16:31.106 --> 01:16:31.826 A:middle
things here.

01:16:31.986 --> 01:16:33.406 A:middle
I'll just point out one of them.

01:16:33.666 --> 01:16:34.946 A:middle
You can read some of your

01:16:34.946 --> 01:16:36.096 A:middle
favorite things up there.

01:16:36.096 --> 01:16:37.316 A:middle
A big request in developers is

01:16:37.316 --> 01:16:38.836 A:middle
called phased releases.

01:16:39.136 --> 01:16:39.516 A:middle
Now when you--

01:16:39.626 --> 01:16:39.796 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Woo!

01:16:39.796 --> 01:16:42.076 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Yes, woo for phased releases,

01:16:42.076 --> 01:16:42.516 A:middle
come on.

01:16:42.686 --> 01:16:44.946 A:middle
Phased releases means, when you

01:16:45.026 --> 01:16:47.156 A:middle
submit an app, you can choose if

01:16:47.196 --> 01:16:48.546 A:middle
you want it to be phased over

01:16:48.546 --> 01:16:49.946 A:middle
time so it doesn't hit your

01:16:49.946 --> 01:16:51.556 A:middle
infrastructure all at once and

01:16:51.556 --> 01:16:52.746 A:middle
you can see how customers are

01:16:52.746 --> 01:16:54.296 A:middle
responding to that update.

01:16:54.596 --> 01:16:56.086 A:middle
So it's really great feature for

01:16:56.086 --> 01:16:57.086 A:middle
you to take advantage of.

01:16:57.086 --> 01:16:58.566 A:middle
And there are a lot of things

01:16:58.616 --> 01:17:00.306 A:middle
coming this year but there is

01:17:00.306 --> 01:17:03.416 A:middle
one that is incredibly gigantic.

01:17:03.996 --> 01:17:04.866 A:middle
And that is we're going to do

01:17:04.896 --> 01:17:06.136 A:middle
something that we've never done

01:17:06.136 --> 01:17:07.176 A:middle
before in the nine years of the

01:17:07.176 --> 01:17:07.716 A:middle
App Store.

01:17:08.156 --> 01:17:09.406 A:middle
We're going to completely

01:17:09.406 --> 01:17:12.256 A:middle
redesign it, a brand new App

01:17:12.256 --> 01:17:12.766 A:middle
Store.

01:17:13.016 --> 01:17:14.066 A:middle
[ Applause ]

01:17:14.066 --> 01:17:15.976 A:middle
It is absolutely beautiful.

01:17:16.516 --> 01:17:19.556 A:middle
[ Applause ]

