[ Music ]

02:05:09.516 --> 02:05:16.986 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

02:05:17.486 --> 02:05:18.896 A:middle
It is absolutely beautiful and

02:05:18.896 --> 02:05:22.006 A:middle
we call it HomePod.

02:05:23.046 --> 02:05:23.826 A:middle
Yes.

02:05:24.516 --> 02:05:26.756 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

02:05:27.256 --> 02:05:29.836 A:middle
Just like iPod reinvented music

02:05:29.836 --> 02:05:32.086 A:middle
in our pockets, HomePod is going

02:05:32.086 --> 02:05:34.736 A:middle
to reinvent music in our homes.

02:05:35.766 --> 02:05:36.796 A:middle
So let's talk about these

02:05:36.796 --> 02:05:37.166 A:middle
features.

02:05:37.166 --> 02:05:38.866 A:middle
First, rock the house.

02:05:39.656 --> 02:05:41.526 A:middle
The HomePod is just under 7

02:05:41.526 --> 02:05:42.676 A:middle
inches tall.

02:05:43.396 --> 02:05:45.436 A:middle
It's covered in a seamless 3D

02:05:45.436 --> 02:05:46.826 A:middle
mesh fabric that has incredible

02:05:46.826 --> 02:05:48.736 A:middle
acoustic properties, and it

02:05:48.736 --> 02:05:51.176 A:middle
hides within it amazing audio

02:05:51.176 --> 02:05:51.926 A:middle
technology.

02:05:53.026 --> 02:05:56.546 A:middle
For example, along the bottom is

02:05:56.786 --> 02:06:00.266 A:middle
a 7 array beam-formed tweeter

02:06:00.266 --> 02:06:01.636 A:middle
pack that's packed with seven

02:06:01.636 --> 02:06:03.216 A:middle
tweeters, each with their own

02:06:03.216 --> 02:06:04.386 A:middle
individual driver.

02:06:04.856 --> 02:06:06.706 A:middle
They're precision acoustic horns

02:06:07.086 --> 02:06:09.126 A:middle
that drive the audio from within

02:06:09.126 --> 02:06:10.736 A:middle
and then out along the bottom

02:06:10.936 --> 02:06:12.306 A:middle
with tremendous directional

02:06:12.346 --> 02:06:12.946 A:middle
control.

02:06:12.946 --> 02:06:14.216 A:middle
And that will become really

02:06:14.216 --> 02:06:15.586 A:middle
clear in a bit as we talk about

02:06:15.586 --> 02:06:16.016 A:middle
how it works.

02:06:17.316 --> 02:06:18.936 A:middle
It has a really big woofer,

02:06:18.936 --> 02:06:20.916 A:middle
4-inch woofer upward facing with

02:06:20.916 --> 02:06:22.276 A:middle
a large motor to move a lot of

02:06:22.276 --> 02:06:22.676 A:middle
air.

02:06:22.676 --> 02:06:23.946 A:middle
It has automatic bass

02:06:23.946 --> 02:06:25.426 A:middle
equalization and dynamic

02:06:25.426 --> 02:06:26.756 A:middle
software modeling so that as we

02:06:26.756 --> 02:06:28.536 A:middle
turn the volume up, it's free

02:06:28.536 --> 02:06:29.356 A:middle
from distortion.

02:06:30.466 --> 02:06:32.886 A:middle
And all of this is controlled by

02:06:32.886 --> 02:06:34.476 A:middle
an Apple A8 chip.

02:06:34.476 --> 02:06:37.146 A:middle
Yes, the same chip that powers

02:06:37.146 --> 02:06:39.506 A:middle
the inside of our iPhone is

02:06:39.506 --> 02:06:40.656 A:middle
inside HomePod.

02:06:41.016 --> 02:06:42.596 A:middle
It's perhaps the biggest brain

02:06:42.596 --> 02:06:44.566 A:middle
ever in a speaker, and it does

02:06:44.566 --> 02:06:45.626 A:middle
some incredible things.

02:06:46.516 --> 02:06:50.916 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

02:06:51.416 --> 02:06:52.906 A:middle
It has real-time acoustic

02:06:52.906 --> 02:06:55.026 A:middle
modeling, audio beam-forming,

02:06:55.186 --> 02:06:56.266 A:middle
and multi-channel echo

02:06:56.266 --> 02:06:56.966 A:middle
cancellation.

02:06:56.966 --> 02:06:58.086 A:middle
You don't have to know any of

02:06:58.086 --> 02:06:59.116 A:middle
that, is just know that it

02:06:59.226 --> 02:07:00.896 A:middle
sounds incredible.

02:07:01.336 --> 02:07:07.496 A:middle
Next, we talk about this spatial

02:07:07.496 --> 02:07:07.946 A:middle
awareness.

02:07:07.946 --> 02:07:08.766 A:middle
Well, what does that mean?

02:07:08.766 --> 02:07:10.686 A:middle
Well, you plug in your HomePod

02:07:10.686 --> 02:07:11.986 A:middle
to AC and it gets its music

02:07:12.056 --> 02:07:12.766 A:middle
wirelessly.

02:07:13.246 --> 02:07:14.446 A:middle
And it's compact enough that you

02:07:14.446 --> 02:07:15.586 A:middle
can put it mostly anywhere in

02:07:15.586 --> 02:07:16.036 A:middle
your house.

02:07:16.036 --> 02:07:17.396 A:middle
You can put it on a table, on a

02:07:17.396 --> 02:07:19.056 A:middle
shelf, against the wall, in a

02:07:19.056 --> 02:07:21.566 A:middle
corner and it intelligently and

02:07:21.566 --> 02:07:23.906 A:middle
automatically detects the spaces

02:07:23.906 --> 02:07:24.316 A:middle
within.

02:07:24.316 --> 02:07:27.476 A:middle
And it uses that information to

02:07:27.476 --> 02:07:29.246 A:middle
adjust the audio, to balance it,

02:07:29.286 --> 02:07:30.846 A:middle
and take full advantage of the

02:07:30.846 --> 02:07:31.936 A:middle
environment and create a very

02:07:31.936 --> 02:07:33.106 A:middle
spacious sound.

02:07:34.406 --> 02:07:35.576 A:middle
Now, we want to give you a sense

02:07:35.576 --> 02:07:37.076 A:middle
of what that experience is like.

02:07:37.636 --> 02:07:39.286 A:middle
So we want to play some music in

02:07:39.286 --> 02:07:41.536 A:middle
this room and show you a visual

02:07:41.536 --> 02:07:43.376 A:middle
simulation to give you an

02:07:43.376 --> 02:07:44.536 A:middle
understanding of some of the

02:07:44.536 --> 02:07:46.006 A:middle
technologies it's using and how

02:07:46.006 --> 02:07:47.646 A:middle
it's adopting them to make

02:07:47.776 --> 02:07:49.116 A:middle
incredible sound, on this

02:07:49.116 --> 02:07:50.146 A:middle
compact speaker.

02:07:50.146 --> 02:07:51.956 A:middle
So I'm going to start by playing

02:07:51.956 --> 02:07:53.736 A:middle
an audio track and it will be a

02:07:53.736 --> 02:07:54.906 A:middle
full mix and then I'm going to

02:07:54.906 --> 02:07:55.846 A:middle
break it down to some of the

02:07:55.846 --> 02:07:57.916 A:middle
components that the HomePod

02:07:57.916 --> 02:07:58.546 A:middle
controls.

02:08:00.516 --> 02:08:13.596 A:middle
[ Music ]

02:08:14.096 --> 02:08:17.326 A:middle
So that's a full rich audio mix

02:08:17.856 --> 02:08:19.466 A:middle
but within it, HomePod detects

02:08:19.636 --> 02:08:21.326 A:middle
the center vocals and can use

02:08:21.406 --> 02:08:22.606 A:middle
beam-forming to direct that.

02:08:23.516 --> 02:08:29.566 A:middle
[ Music ]

02:08:30.066 --> 02:08:32.236 A:middle
It gives incredible clarity and

02:08:32.336 --> 02:08:32.926 A:middle
precision.

02:08:32.926 --> 02:08:34.096 A:middle
And then it can detect something

02:08:34.096 --> 02:08:35.496 A:middle
called direct energy with the

02:08:35.496 --> 02:08:37.336 A:middle
instrumentation and direct that

02:08:37.336 --> 02:08:38.296 A:middle
in the room as well.

02:08:39.516 --> 02:08:47.586 A:middle
[ Music ]

02:08:48.086 --> 02:08:49.986 A:middle
In addition to that direct

02:08:49.986 --> 02:08:51.516 A:middle
energy, there's something that's

02:08:51.516 --> 02:08:52.656 A:middle
usually missing in music,

02:08:52.746 --> 02:08:55.056 A:middle
ambient audio, the backing

02:08:55.056 --> 02:08:55.976 A:middle
vocals and reverb.

02:08:56.516 --> 02:09:05.536 A:middle
[ Music ]

02:09:06.036 --> 02:09:07.606 A:middle
HomePod can direct all of these

02:09:07.606 --> 02:09:09.306 A:middle
and pull it together to a full

02:09:09.306 --> 02:09:11.016 A:middle
rich mix that fills up your

02:09:11.016 --> 02:09:11.196 A:middle
room.

02:09:12.516 --> 02:09:22.516 A:middle
[ Music ]

02:09:23.516 --> 02:09:28.486 A:middle
[ Applause and Cheering ]

02:09:28.986 --> 02:09:30.126 A:middle
It's a really remarkable

02:09:30.126 --> 02:09:31.446 A:middle
experience to hear this kind of

02:09:31.446 --> 02:09:33.326 A:middle
a spacious sound come from such

02:09:33.326 --> 02:09:34.356 A:middle
a compact speaker.

02:09:34.356 --> 02:09:36.506 A:middle
And if you love one, you should

02:09:36.506 --> 02:09:37.606 A:middle
see what it's like when you set

02:09:37.606 --> 02:09:39.126 A:middle
up two and they automatically

02:09:39.126 --> 02:09:40.176 A:middle
work together to give this

02:09:40.236 --> 02:09:42.096 A:middle
incredible spacious sound that

02:09:42.096 --> 02:09:43.766 A:middle
really has the power to rock

02:09:43.766 --> 02:09:44.336 A:middle
your house.

02:09:44.926 --> 02:09:48.086 A:middle
Next, a musicologist.

02:09:48.416 --> 02:09:50.396 A:middle
This intelligent helper to help

02:09:50.396 --> 02:09:52.416 A:middle
us discover the music we love.

02:09:53.536 --> 02:09:56.956 A:middle
HomePod has an incredible

02:09:56.956 --> 02:09:58.316 A:middle
speaker system that works

02:09:58.316 --> 02:10:00.556 A:middle
together with our Apple Music

02:10:00.556 --> 02:10:01.246 A:middle
subscription.

02:10:01.246 --> 02:10:02.356 A:middle
From the beginning, it's

02:10:02.356 --> 02:10:02.976 A:middle
designed to work with that.

02:10:03.076 --> 02:10:05.646 A:middle
Now, Apple Music as you know

02:10:05.646 --> 02:10:07.316 A:middle
provides music in the cloud and

02:10:07.316 --> 02:10:08.176 A:middle
if the speaker can get it

02:10:08.176 --> 02:10:10.366 A:middle
directly from the cloud, it can

02:10:10.366 --> 02:10:12.166 A:middle
get 40 million tracks, two

02:10:12.166 --> 02:10:13.116 A:middle
million artists, tens of

02:10:13.116 --> 02:10:14.176 A:middle
thousands of playlists.

02:10:14.176 --> 02:10:15.756 A:middle
But not just any music library,

02:10:15.756 --> 02:10:17.226 A:middle
this is your music library.

02:10:17.386 --> 02:10:18.536 A:middle
It knows the playlists you've

02:10:18.536 --> 02:10:20.006 A:middle
set up, it knows the artist you

02:10:20.006 --> 02:10:21.846 A:middle
love and all of them stream

02:10:21.846 --> 02:10:23.986 A:middle
directly to your HomePod.

02:10:24.846 --> 02:10:27.086 A:middle
It works with an array of six

02:10:27.086 --> 02:10:28.486 A:middle
microphones around the middle,

02:10:28.486 --> 02:10:30.536 A:middle
so as you talk to it and you say

02:10:30.536 --> 02:10:33.056 A:middle
those magic words, "Hey Siri,"

02:10:33.056 --> 02:10:35.536 A:middle
you see a waveform light up on

02:10:35.536 --> 02:10:37.406 A:middle
top and now it can respond to

02:10:37.556 --> 02:10:39.096 A:middle
your commands and help serve up

02:10:39.096 --> 02:10:40.516 A:middle
the music you want to hear.

02:10:42.736 --> 02:10:44.326 A:middle
The Siri team has worked very

02:10:44.326 --> 02:10:46.396 A:middle
hard to adapt the domain of

02:10:46.396 --> 02:10:48.386 A:middle
music in Siri to be even greater

02:10:48.386 --> 02:10:50.156 A:middle
and understand more of the

02:10:50.156 --> 02:10:51.186 A:middle
questions we're going to ask

02:10:51.306 --> 02:10:51.926 A:middle
about music.

02:10:52.206 --> 02:10:53.436 A:middle
Simple things obviously like

02:10:53.596 --> 02:10:54.756 A:middle
Play Beats 1 Radio.

02:10:55.236 --> 02:10:56.426 A:middle
We all want to do that.

02:10:56.426 --> 02:10:57.906 A:middle
Or play "I'm Poppy".

02:10:58.236 --> 02:10:59.216 A:middle
Check it out if you don't know

02:10:59.216 --> 02:10:59.916 A:middle
what that's about.

02:11:01.026 --> 02:11:02.326 A:middle
Play something new.

02:11:02.326 --> 02:11:03.486 A:middle
Who's singing on this track?

02:11:03.486 --> 02:11:04.576 A:middle
Something I ask all the time.

02:11:04.576 --> 02:11:05.756 A:middle
Who's playing drums on this

02:11:05.756 --> 02:11:06.086 A:middle
track?

02:11:06.416 --> 02:11:07.846 A:middle
To complex questions like, what

02:11:07.846 --> 02:11:09.736 A:middle
was the top song on May 5th,

02:11:09.736 --> 02:11:11.216 A:middle
2016.

02:11:11.436 --> 02:11:13.336 A:middle
You just play more like that or

02:11:13.336 --> 02:11:14.446 A:middle
I like that song.

02:11:15.236 --> 02:11:16.276 A:middle
It's a free form.

02:11:16.406 --> 02:11:17.886 A:middle
Siri doesn't need a specific

02:11:17.886 --> 02:11:18.526 A:middle
list of commands.

02:11:18.526 --> 02:11:19.816 A:middle
It can interpret what you're

02:11:19.816 --> 02:11:21.746 A:middle
saying and help you discover the

02:11:21.746 --> 02:11:22.526 A:middle
music you love.

02:11:23.226 --> 02:11:24.586 A:middle
And even better, you don't have

02:11:24.586 --> 02:11:26.696 A:middle
to just sit next to the HomePod

02:11:26.696 --> 02:11:27.426 A:middle
to talk to it.

02:11:27.426 --> 02:11:29.446 A:middle
It can be across the room and

02:11:29.446 --> 02:11:31.046 A:middle
speak to the HomePod even while

02:11:31.046 --> 02:11:32.636 A:middle
loud music is playing and the

02:11:32.636 --> 02:11:33.476 A:middle
speaker array and the

02:11:33.476 --> 02:11:35.156 A:middle
microphones can pick it up and

02:11:35.156 --> 02:11:36.036 A:middle
hear what you're saying.

02:11:37.196 --> 02:11:39.816 A:middle
So HomePod, it has the power to

02:11:39.816 --> 02:11:42.116 A:middle
rock the house in a spatial

02:11:42.116 --> 02:11:43.476 A:middle
awareness so that it understands

02:11:43.476 --> 02:11:45.306 A:middle
the rooms we place it within.

02:11:45.306 --> 02:11:47.736 A:middle
And it has the fun interactivity

02:11:47.736 --> 02:11:49.686 A:middle
of Siri becoming a musicologist

02:11:49.836 --> 02:11:51.176 A:middle
and helping us to listen to the

02:11:51.176 --> 02:11:51.976 A:middle
music we love.

02:11:51.976 --> 02:11:53.866 A:middle
And since Siri is built in there

02:11:53.866 --> 02:11:55.366 A:middle
and you can speak to it, well,

02:11:55.366 --> 02:11:56.546 A:middle
the team has also worked hard to

02:11:56.546 --> 02:11:58.476 A:middle
make it a great and helpful home

02:11:58.476 --> 02:11:59.836 A:middle
assistant as well.

02:11:59.966 --> 02:12:03.316 A:middle
We said the domain of music is

02:12:03.316 --> 02:12:04.636 A:middle
something Siri knows really well

02:12:04.636 --> 02:12:05.226 A:middle
in HomePod.

02:12:05.296 --> 02:12:07.096 A:middle
There are other domains as well.

02:12:07.256 --> 02:12:08.176 A:middle
We've worked hard to pick the

02:12:08.396 --> 02:12:09.706 A:middle
first ones that we think matter

02:12:09.706 --> 02:12:11.346 A:middle
most in a product like HomePod,

02:12:11.346 --> 02:12:12.636 A:middle
so of course, it can play your

02:12:12.636 --> 02:12:13.266 A:middle
podcasts.

02:12:13.266 --> 02:12:15.386 A:middle
But it can also do things like

02:12:15.736 --> 02:12:17.626 A:middle
give you news, give you weather,

02:12:17.626 --> 02:12:18.896 A:middle
traffic, sports.

02:12:18.896 --> 02:12:20.206 A:middle
You can ask it to set a

02:12:20.206 --> 02:12:23.286 A:middle
reminder, set a timer, text

02:12:23.286 --> 02:12:24.486 A:middle
someone with messages.

02:12:24.876 --> 02:12:26.436 A:middle
And if you have HomeKit devices

02:12:26.436 --> 02:12:27.446 A:middle
set up in your home, you can

02:12:27.446 --> 02:12:28.776 A:middle
speak to your HomePod and

02:12:28.776 --> 02:12:30.506 A:middle
control your HomeKit devices.

02:12:31.176 --> 02:12:34.716 A:middle
So for example, for the HomePod

02:12:34.716 --> 02:12:36.636 A:middle
set up, you can say, "When do

02:12:36.636 --> 02:12:37.956 A:middle
the Red Sox play next?"

