They're going to beat the

02:12:39.096 --> 02:12:39.966 A:middle
Yankees, trust me.

02:12:40.696 --> 02:12:43.836 A:middle
Tune to NPR instead, flip a

02:12:43.836 --> 02:12:45.596 A:middle
coin, remind me to bring snacks

02:12:45.596 --> 02:12:46.226 A:middle
to a party.

02:12:46.806 --> 02:12:49.106 A:middle
You can set up reminders, check

02:12:49.106 --> 02:12:50.646 A:middle
all the sports news and weather,

02:12:51.006 --> 02:12:52.416 A:middle
all directly with your voice,

02:12:52.656 --> 02:12:53.846 A:middle
talk to a HomePod that gets the

02:12:53.846 --> 02:12:55.496 A:middle
information directly from the

02:12:55.496 --> 02:12:55.926 A:middle
cloud.

02:12:55.996 --> 02:12:58.196 A:middle
And if you have HomeKit devices

02:12:58.196 --> 02:12:59.826 A:middle
set up, you can say simple

02:12:59.826 --> 02:13:01.556 A:middle
things like, are the lights on,

02:13:01.896 --> 02:13:03.776 A:middle
turn the heat up, turn on the

02:13:03.776 --> 02:13:05.396 A:middle
air conditioning, bring the

02:13:05.396 --> 02:13:08.026 A:middle
shades down halfway, turn off

02:13:08.026 --> 02:13:09.456 A:middle
the lights in the bedroom.

02:13:10.076 --> 02:13:11.466 A:middle
And if you've set up scenes in

02:13:11.466 --> 02:13:12.736 A:middle
HomeKit you can control those as

02:13:12.736 --> 02:13:13.146 A:middle
well.

02:13:13.356 --> 02:13:14.696 A:middle
You can say, "I'm home.

02:13:15.146 --> 02:13:16.036 A:middle
It's movie time.

02:13:16.036 --> 02:13:17.466 A:middle
I'm leaving now."

02:13:17.466 --> 02:13:18.696 A:middle
And the whole scene can

